(407, 'Skateboard-City Rules and Info', 'Please Note: Once signed up, in your control panel, you can hide your e-mail address and select other options to prevent spam\r\n\r\nActions Prohibited:\r\n-Excessively overusing swear words in your posts\r\n-Posting virus/hacks\r\n-Posting links to porn or obscene websites\r\n-Mistreating any members\r\n-Posting pictures of obscene things\r\n-Making usernames to imitate other members OR Having multiple accounts OR giving out passwords.\r\n-Spamming/Flooding (Such as, clicking the "Post" button several times to get\r\nhigher rank or for amusement)\r\n-Posting useless topics/polls\r\n-Posting topics/polls in wrong categories\r\n-Spamming to people with Personal Messages\r\n-Sending PMs with advertisements (your site, messageboard, etc.)\r\n-Any form of obtrusive advertising on any part of the site. (If you want to advertise, please contact me about rates)\r\n-Do not post a topic, if there''s another similar topic already active\r\n-Posting threads just to introduce yourself*\r\n-Putting ridiculously large picture(s) in your signature/for your avatar\r\n-Posting numerous amount of smilies in your post\r\n-Continuously quote posts\r\n-Any involvement of rule breaking or sabotage (such as Spam Attacks) on other forums, will jeopardize your membership here as much as it should there.\r\n-Unnecessary "bumping" of topics\r\n-Misusing the reputation system\r\n-Posting sensitive information of other members or people such as phone numbers and postal addresses.\r\n-Posting random lyrics not related at all to a thread (this will be considered spam).\r\n*It may seem a little odd, but we get far too many members signing up every day for any introduction threads to be worthwhile. Read through the rules, make good posts and people will notice you.\r\n\r\nConsequences:\r\n-Warnings (depending of level of actions done)\r\n-Negative Reputation\r\n-Posts moved\r\n-Posts deleted\r\n-User deletion\r\n-User Banning\r\n-IP banning\r\n\r\nThreads you probably shouldn''t make...\r\nAlthough not prohibited, its a very good idea not to re-make any of the following threads. They have been done countless times and will not offer anymore interesting discussion. It will also tend to bring a negative reaction from members here.\r\n\r\n- "Who is better out of Rodney Mullen and Daewon Song"\r\n- "Why do people hate skateboarders"\r\n- most threads with the main topic of "posers"\r\n- posting footage of Mullens sections from either Round 1, 2, 3, Opinion, Questionable or THPS games; posting footage of the leap of faith; the 900; the el-toro kickflip... pretty much any of the really well known skateboarding clips as they have been posted many times before.\r\n\r\nActions Encouraged:\r\n-Making intelligent, well thought-out posts\r\n-Being funny without being stupid or annoying\r\n-Respecting one another''s opinions\r\n-Not being aggressive over others opinions or actions\r\n-Using correct spelling and grammar\r\n-Generally being a mature and helpful member\r\n\r\nOther Rules:\r\n-Accounts with 0 posts will be deleted every few months\r\n-Go to the F.A.Q.s on the top Navigation Bar, and read and understand them,\r\nbefore asking questions about the Message Board.\r\n-Try to use the search function to find things before posting to prevent many similar topics\r\n-When mods deem that you are bringing down the general atmosphere and "good" of the forum, you are subject to banning.\r\n\r\nBy: Agent/Admin, revised by Roboman', 235, 0, '2007-01-19 13:00:00'),
