(445, 'My bearing cleaning procedure', 'I clean my bearings whenever I feel like i''m going too slow. When I clean them, here is the procedure:\r\n\r\n1. Take shields off\r\n2: Get a bowl\r\n3: Mix 50% Isopryl alcohol with Nail polish remover ( acetone) and fresh water (prefer fiji )\r\n4: drop bearings ball side up in the solution\r\n5: let them sit for 1-2 hours (this cuts all the grease and dirt and grime. explained later)\r\n6: take them out.\r\n7. Get a fine haired brush with handle, and with running water on both, grab a bearings and start brushing the shit out of it with the brush.\r\n8. This gets at all dirt, rust, and oil, + grime. It''s crazy how black my hands are after it.\r\n9. Lube them up with speed cream, and pop em in the wheels.\r\n\r\nHow do you clean your bearings?', 470, 0, '2013-09-01 13:00:00'),
