(517, 'A shoe guide. ( NEW )', 'Ok heres the deal, only participate if you are going to give a detailed review and if you have them. I''m tired of seeing the same topics over and over again, so heres how this shoe guide works. Name shoes you have tried ( Brand and model ) and give a detailed review about them. If people participate in this, we wont see so many topics about the same shoes. Well here goes mine.\r\n\r\nEs Accels- The grip lasts along time, they rip and all, but there is a rubber layer under the leather or suede, so thats a clue when to shoe goo the shoes. Also, they are very comfortable.\r\n\r\nEmerica Ellingtons- One of the best shoes I have ever had. Rubber layer under suede, good grip, and it actually lasts sort of long. They are comfortable and take impact well, but they are a bit bulky.\r\n\r\nEmerica Ellington 2s- Comfortable shoe. Loses grip fast and rips pretty easy.\r\n\r\nEmerica Kirchart 3- Horrible, grip lasted a week before it completley flattened out, ripped easy, lace guards and laces all ripped in a couple days.\r\n\r\nEs accelerates- Most comfortable shoe ever. Too bad I ended up sending them back due to a big air bubble in the sole and how the sole fell off.\r\n\r\nNike Dunks- Comfortable, durable, good grip, great boardfeel. Overall great shoe.\r\n\r\nGlobe chet thomas ( the bulky ass shoes )- Bad feel, grip lasts 2 weeks, sort of durable, very comfortable.\r\n\r\nDC avatar- Lasted me the whole summer I started skating in.\r\n\r\nVans XLTs- I dont remember because they were the first shoes I ever had. I remember grip going away fast and a hole in the shoe completely in like 3 weeks?\r\n\r\nDVS Revivals- Grip didnt last long. Good feel. Not durable\r\n\r\nOk, now post on.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n( The old shoe guide got messed up and started freezing peoples computers, so lets try it again. )', 1128, 0, '2006-01-14 13:00:00'),
