(168, 'Good idea. I actually longboard more than regular board anymore an I know a bunch of members who longboard, so I think a new section would work well.', 406, 183, 0, '2010-11-26 07:30:00'),
(169, 'You can buy complete "toy" skateboards/, made in places like Taiwan/, in the appropriate shops. Here we''re talking about the cost of what we would call a "real" skateboard/, all of them made in the USA. There is a vast difference in terms of performance.', 406, 182, 1, '2010-11-26 07:30:00'),
(170, 'Wood decks are made out of plain maple laminates. Slick boards have a layer of slippery plastic bonded to the bottom.', 406, 186, 1, '2010-11-27 07:30:00'),
(171, 'Longboarding is working Smooth\n\r\nThe groms in my neighborhood are all about the soft wheels and carving.', 406, 184, 0, '2010-11-29 07:30:00'),
(172, 'I never have been on a longboard, how is it different from a regular skateboard, it longboarding alot harder?', 406, 185, 0, '2010-11-29 07:30:00'),
(173, 'You can have just wood/, but not just the slick part. Slick on wood if you require extra slide/strength. Slick decks are usually heavier than wood ones', 406, 186, 1, '2010-11-29 07:30:00'),
(174, 'Sick video DVS! Kyle Martin shreds.\r\n\r\nI''ve recently found a new a new great place to longboard. Golf cart paths in the off season are narrow, bendy, steep, smooth and deserted. I recommend finding a nice path to go skate as they''re perfect 5/12 of the year to shred (at least where I''m from).', 406, 183, 0, '2010-11-30 07:30:00'),
(175, 'Wheel sizes plunged below 40mm in the early nineties/, but since then they''ve increased again. ', 406, 182, 1, '2010-11-30 07:30:00'),
(176, 'I love heelside standies so. Very Sketchy ', 406, 186, 1, '2010-11-30 07:30:00'),
(177, 'Earthwing <3. Ugh I was gonna go longboard today but it started pouring, so I guess I''m going to have to wait until Sunday. I need a new pair of sliding gloves, I lost my old ones and I made some ghetto ones but they are so damn uncomfortable. Posi to anyone who can link me to a good, new, cheap pair of sliding gloves.', 406, 183, 0, '2010-11-30 07:30:00'),
(178, 'Small ones or none for small wheels.', 406, 186, 1, '2010-11-30 07:30:00'),
(179, 'Quote:\r\nOriginally Posted by Mark\nLandyachtz have been my favorite so far. Loaded''s suck. I''ve heard the Sector9 gloves (the leather ones) aren''t bad either.\r\n\r\nOr, you could buy a pair of Mechanix from Home Depot and just buy pucks. I recommend Phat Deanz, Black Velvets, or Ojooms.\r\n\r\nAlso, Earthwing FTW. I have a Mystery Model, Belly Racer, Supermodel, and Corchia. I also have waaaaay too many boards haha. Other than the EW''s I listed above, I have an Evo, Nemesis, Apex 37 (regretfully), and two Sector Nines.\r\nI have some Sector 9 gloves and they are alright, and I agree about the Loaded gloves. They are sooo uncomfortable.\r\n\r\nWhy is there still no longboarding section', 406, 182, 1, '2010-11-30 07:30:00'),
(180, 'Sadly, I don''t there are enough members who longboard for the section to be made, but who knows. It''d be awesome if they did make one.\r\n\r\nAlso, to those of you who longboard, do you guys wear helmets?\r\n\r\nI personally have ever since I got a concussion in March doing a toeside 180. I got highsided, hit my head, and couldn''t do anything for two months. Wearing one has saved me from head injuries numerous times since.', 406, 186, 1, '2010-11-30 07:30:00'),
