(228, 'Quote:\r\nOriginally Posted by Colten\n... How quick does it take for them to get speed wobbles, if they get any?\r\nWobs come from you, not the board. Keep your front foot planted on top of the front truck and don''t ride it "popsicle style" with all your weight on the back of the board. Your wheels roll over things and you don''t need to wheelie over specks of dust, so your stance should be on the front 2/3 of the deck if it''s over 38" and front 4/5 if it''s shorter. Steer off the front truck, like a car (instead of the rear one, like a fork lift) and if you get wobbly, pressure that front foot by bending the front knee --you''re not leaning over the front of the board but putting weight on that truck. Wobs gone!', 406, 184, 0, '2011-03-07 07:30:00'),
