INSERT INTO `responses` (`id`, `content`, `postid`, `userid`, `havemedia`, `response_timestamp`) VALUES
(312, 'Sector 9 centerset Raceforms are fucking awesome. I picked up some 82a one''s today, and I''m pretty blown away. So far, they feel like an icier, but still as buttery Abec 11 Freeride that wears slower.', 406, 186, 1, '2011-07-04 07:30:00'),
(313, 'Bump to say I got a Nelson Spindrift, and it''s such an awesome board. It has the best concave I''ve ever felt. The concave carries into the half inch drop (it''s the only wood board to be able to do this, every other wooden drop deck loses the concave at the drop), and mixed with a subtle w concave, it just feels so awesome.', 406, 186, 1, '2011-08-04 07:30:00'),
(314, 'Is it too drifty with the dropthru? I am looking at both that and the topspin.', 406, 183, 0, '2011-08-04 07:30:00'),
(315, 'Quote:\r\nOriginally Posted by Leon\nIs it too drifty with the dropthru? I am looking at both that and the topspin.\r\nIt''s definitely drifty, but it''s nothing crazy. I was debating between the two and decided to go Spindrift since you have the option to topmount it, granted it''ll have a bit more torsional flex.\r\n\r\nYou really can''t go wrong though. The concave just cups your feet.', 406, 186, 1, '2011-08-04 07:30:00'),
(316, 'i''m going to college pretty soon and wanted a longboard to get around campus. can anyone suggest me the right board for this? nothing too big either', 406, 218, 0, '2011-08-15 07:30:00'),
(317, 'i just got a longboard today.\r\n\r\nshit''s pretty fly.', 406, 219, 0, '2011-08-15 07:30:00'),
(318, 'i have a 30 inch cruiser tht i used last year to skate to class, i''d reccomend that size. anything over 40 inches and you''re a fag, its quite obvious after being on campus for 1 semester. the next semester you''ll start to think that everyone skating to class is a fag, but continue to do it anyway cause it''s convenient.', 406, 204, 0, '2011-08-15 07:30:00'),
(319, 'Quote:\r\nOriginally Posted by Lukas\ni''m going to college pretty soon and wanted a longboard to get around campus. can anyone suggest me the right board for this? nothing too big either\r\nPick the shape you like, because part of longboarding is that you''re not constrained to be a clone... but here are some things you want:\r\n\r\n--70 or 76mm wheels, 78a or softer: fast, smooth, grippy and roll right over stuff that has the toy board guys walking and carrying their boards.\r\n\r\n--38-42" inch deck. Longer than that, and you''ll have issues moving around the library or in lines, etc... with it. Shorter than that and you''ll miss out on the stability and room you want on campus and especially when you skate with books in your bag... which you will. Don''t worry about whether it fits under a desk/chair, because you''ll tilt it against the wall in the lecture halls, no problem.\r Mongo\n\r\n--Actual longboard trucks, like Randal, Paris, Gunmetal, Caliber, Bear, etc... rather than just "wide old school trucks" like large Indys, etc... Hey, big Indys are fun, but there''s a reason Randal-style trucks rule and it''s the super stable yet turny design that makes a longboard so agile and smooth.\r\n\r\nSo, check out DeVille completes, Stella completes, and Gravity completes for cool longboards you can skate the hell out of and not be too bummed when you bash em up and ride em through puddles on the walking path, etc... Those are budget-boards with quality. Want to spend more (oh, you will later... ), then bump up to Landyachtz, Never Summer, Bustin, etc...', 406, 184, 0, '2011-08-16 07:30:00'),
(320, 'Quote:\r\nOriginally Posted by Felix\ni''m going to college pretty soon and wanted a longboard to get around campus. can anyone suggest me the right board for this? nothing too big either\r\nSomething light and with a kicktail would definitely be useful. The Earthwing Miniglider or Superglider would be perfect, depending on what size board you''re after. The Miniglider is 33in, the Superglider is 38in. Both boards are pretty much made for Indy 169''s, though you can run 180mm reverse kingpin trucks like Randal, Paris, etc on the Superglider.\r\n\r\n\r\nMiniglider^\r\n\r\n\r\nSuperglider^\r\n\r\nOh and I would avoid Bustin, as their boards aren''t the most durable...', 406, 186, 1, '2011-08-16 07:30:00'),
