(1249, 'Only you can answer that. I''m about 5''9", 150 lbs, and have size 8 shoes. In 6 months back on a board I came to the conclusion that I wanted a smaller deck, different wheels and bearings than I was riding. Here are videos of my 2 favorite skaters:\r\nhttp://m.youtube.com/watch?v=xBvGzObIZsQ\r\n\r\nhttp://m.youtube.com/watch?v=cbSbbY5ibas\r\n\r\nI slowly realized as I was progressing I realized that I had to change a couple of things in my set up to make what I was trying for easier. This is way too heavy a conversation to get into with a beginner. Lets just say taste and preferences are fluid and subjective.', 434, 466, 0, '2013-10-30 07:30:00'),
(1250, 'Quote:\r\nOriginally Posted by antipop\r\nI don''t have a helmet. My head is 23  inches. I''m not sure what my hat size is.\r\n\r\n\r\nI don''t have elbow pads, knee pads, or wrist guards either. I will wear them though- they''ll make me more comfortable, confident and enable myself to push myself harder. I don''t really care about looking cool or anything. I bet I will get bullied at the skatepark or when I''m riding around, but I don''t care. I just think it''d be a good time. I''m all about having fun. I''m not trying to be a pro or anything- though I do think it would be cool to shoot videos and use songs from my favorite bands in the back ground.\r\n\r\nOh and I don''t care what the graphics look like, as long as they ride good.\r\nWhat do you think about this one? http://www.s-onestore.com/servlet/th...t--dsh-/Detail I saw that you''re a Misfits fan. It''s a brand new design for 2013, just came out. I have one, new in the box, never worn. The only thing is the one I have is 22.5" (Hat Size: 7 1/4), which is an XL according to their site. It does come with both XXL (23") and XXXL (23.5") sizing liners so you might be able to make it work. It''s yours if you think it will fit.', 434, 480, 1, '2013-10-31 07:30:00'),
