(1262, 'Quote:\r\nOriginally Posted by Madalynn\nI''m going to suggest Spitfire Formula Fours. Classic 99, 54mm. I have Bones STF''s right now (52) and honestly as fun as they are to slide on they aren''t that smooth, plasticy feeling... Theres a thread on the F4''s somewhere here and everybody loves them. I say 99 not 101 because I don''t think a new rider needs hard ass wheels that slide out too easy.\r\nI wonder if there''s a difference between the red ones and the blue ones.\r\n\r\nUPDATE: I looked on their website and found out the difference.\r\n\r\nThe reds = the 101''s\r\nFORMULATED FOR A HARDER-FASTER RIDE\r\nUNMATCHED FLATSPOT RESISTANCE\r\nSMOOTH ANTI-STICK SLIDE\r\nMORE SPEED AND CONTROL\r\n100% TRUE PERFORMANCE URETHANE\r\nThe blues = 99''s\r\nMore SPEED AND CONTROL on all surfaces\r\nUNMATCHED FLATSPOT RESISTANCE\r\nSMOOTH ANTI-STICK SLIDE\r\nHigh rebound compound\r\n100% TRUE PERFORMANCE URETHANE', 434, 477, 0, '2013-10-31 07:30:00'),
