(1267, 'Quote:\r\nOriginally Posted by Meredith\nI read that Real, Krooked, Anti-Hero, Venture, Thunder, Spitfire and DLXSF are all made by Deluxe Distribution-\r\n\r\nWould that mean that Krooked decks, Anti-Hero decks, Real decks, etc are all the same? Seems like I can''t go wrong as long as I go with a deck made by Deluxe Distribution. Let me know what you think. I appreciate every response that I''ve got. Every post is helpful.\r\nThe only decks that are all ade EXAClY the same are decks like almost, blind, enjoi, and any other deck made at DSM. Its all about their special deck press molds.. this will exxplain :)\r\n\r\nhttp://m.youtube.com/watch?v=FOtbEfdfk9o\r\n\r\nBut the factory is in china and you wanna ride american. So its up to you.. there all made of canadian maple and I personaly think chinese workers take a lot more pride in quality than the average american union worker that knows they can cut any corner they want and not get fired.. just sayin..', 434, 481, 0, '2013-11-02 07:30:00'),
