(1356, 'Quote:\r\nOriginally Posted by Francis\nRubbing Alcohol\r\n+1, use no less than 99% pure.\r\n\r\nQuote:\r\nOriginally Posted by shakejunk\r\nObviously it oxsodizes right away, but I make sure I immediately dry them. I don''t like knowing I left nail polisher remover on my bearings. Just dry them immediately with compressed air and your good.\r\nNo, you don''t even use nail polish remover in the first place. Rubbing alcohol has physical and chemical properties that better suit the job you''re trying to accomplish.\r\n\r\nWhich one dries faster? Rubbing alcohol.\r\nWhich one will not react with metal? Rubbing alcohol.\r\n\r\nWhat you are saying is like trying to unlock a locked door with the wrong key, knowing that the right key is right there on the table.', 445, 272, 1, '2013-09-07 07:30:00'),
