(1360, 'Quote:\r\nOriginally Posted by shakejunk\r\nI like a deep clean. Acetone is recommended on the bones bearing speed creem and bones cleaning kit. I don''t think bones lies about bearings cleaning products. it may get a little oxodized but It''s still is a lot cleaner than just dipping it in alcohol and and popping them in your wheels.\r\n\r\nWhat your saying is like being a successful business. You can take a safe route, and make little money, or you could take a risky route and make more money.\r\nIt doesn''t mean bones is correct. Show me proof of a physical/chemical advantage acetone has over pure alcohol to clean bearings.', 445, 272, 1, '2013-09-09 07:30:00'),
