(1394, 'I''ve watched the Carrasco footage. Even though I consider myself a freestyle skater on a bigger board it bored the shit out of me. Yes 142 360s is an impressive feat reading a little more about it makes it slightly less impressive. For his "Spinner" set up he had a special set of wheels made that are stainless steel and shaped like roller blade wheels (less surface area+harder wheels=less friction) combined with abec 11 bearings designed to rotate thousands of times per second makes it a little less impressive. Plus 5 minutes of a guy spinning in place gets redundant (kind of like this post). Fortunately they cut out the part where he is vomiting from motion sickness.', 446, 466, 0, '2013-07-25 07:30:00'),
(1395, 'Quote:\r\nOriginally Posted by Amya\nI''m pretty sure "gravitational axis" isn''t even a real thing\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nWhere''s this source where Rodney said that 360 spins make manuals much easier? I''d like to see it.\r\n\r\nIt is comprised of moments of inertia of the body about an axis passing through point.This leaves only the gravitational force which exerts a moment on the body. The center of rotation can be calculated but it may be over your head. um... it''s A real thing....\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nhave you seen rodney''s 360''s? Do you think it is mere coincidence his balance and control are by accident? I think not.', 446, 464, 0, '2013-08-01 07:30:00'),
(1396, 'No, the reason why he''s so good at balance and control is because he does caspers a lot\r\n\r\nDoing caspers develop balance using only your center of weight, not relying on any other angular forces to help you maintain equilibrium of your body like 360s do. Learning this makes manuals much easier to learn. Ask Mr Mullen...\r\n\r\nIf you do need to rely on only angular force to keep you afloat, then your newton-euler moment equation about an arbitrary moment center for 360s would have: r (cross product) m*a = 0. This does not apply with manuals because you are not under a fixed axis of rotation, just like caspers. The total moment taking account both angular and linear can be calculated but it may be over your head.\r\n\r\nhave you seen rodney''s caspers? Do you think it is mere coincidence his balance and control are by accident? I think not.\r\n\r\nQuote:\r\nOriginally Posted by boneite\r\nThe center of rotation can be calculated but it may be over your head.\r\nI just calculated the center of rotation to be .12m of a 360 spin\r\nGreat, what can we do with this information? What point did I prove?... absolutely nothing!\r\nAmazing\r\n\r\nLet''s now transform the center of rotation from t-space to s-space using bernoulli''s equation for no reason at all but an attempt to make someone on the internet feel stupid. Will this prove my point? No, but I will sure sound all smart and authoritative! Let''s do it!', 446, 443, 0, '2013-08-02 07:30:00'),
(1397, 'Quote:\r\nOriginally Posted by MikeM\r\nNo, the reason why he''s so good at balance and control is because he does caspers a lot\r\n\r\nDoing caspers develop balance using only your center of weight, not relying on any other angular forces to help you maintain equilibrium of your body like 360s do. Learning this makes manuals much easier to learn. Ask Mr Mullen...\r\n\r\nIf you do need to rely on only angular force to keep you afloat, then your newton-euler moment equation about an arbitrary moment center for 360s would have: r (cross product) m*a = 0. This does not apply with manuals because you are not under a fixed axis of rotation, just like caspers. The total moment taking account both angular and linear can be calculated but it may be over your head.\r\n\r\nhave you seen rodney''s caspers? Do you think it is mere coincidence his balance and control are by accident? I think not.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nI just calculated the center of rotation to be .12m of a 360 spin\r\nGreat, what can we do with this information? What point did I prove?... absolutely nothing!\r\nAmazing\r\n\r\nLet''s now transform the center of rotation from t-space to s-space using bernoulli''s equation for no reason at all but an attempt to make someone on the internet feel stupid. Will this prove my point? No, but I will sure sound all smart and authoritative! Let''s do it!\r\nDo you know what A g turn is? Please integrate this into your calculation. Oh! and some guy named Per Welinder told me to do more 360''s.', 446, 464, 0, '2013-08-02 07:30:00'),
(1398, 'very sorry, I just calculated the center of rotation to be .125m of a 360 spin\r\nwhat do I do with this\r\n\r\nQuote:\r\nOriginally Posted by boneite\r\nOh! and some guy named Per Welinder told me to do more 360''s.\r\n360s are just a staple in freestyle runs and videos\r\n\r\nIf you want to be good at manuals, do more manuals\r\nLike if you want to be good at nh 50/50s, doing more capsers is stupid, do more nh 50/50s\r\n\r\n\r\nand please stop thinking I''m retarded and I don''t skate freestyle\r\nI''m a mechanical engineer and I''ve been freestyling since I was 13, I was there during wfsa forum times, thanks', 446, 443, 0, '2013-08-03 07:30:00'),
(1399, 'Look Bonite I''m a beginning freestyle skater on a street board. Actually at 6 months back on a board I''m pretty much a beginner again. What drew me to freestyle is a combination of the artistry and I see it as a fantastic way to develop balance and coordination. To me the whole competitive mindset of "How many 360s can you do?" And the tone of your responses are almost the antithesis of the artistic nature of the style.\r\n\r\nDon''t get me wrong I dig Sean Burkes skating but in the interviews I''ve read with him he comes across as an arrogant prick ("I can do 540 Impossibles Mullen couldn''t"). He''s a great skater but I wouldn''t want to hang out with him. The tone of your posts show that you are on the way to having that attitude too. Chill out. This supposed to be fun.', 446, 466, 0, '2013-08-03 07:30:00'),
(1400, 'How many 360''s can you do....It was A light hearted question. I have found that newer skaters don''t learn the fundementals anymore. I see kids trying tricks that require phenominal balance. After watching A kids try these same tricks A zillion times with no success, I realized that mastering fundementals may help that skater succeed. I had no harmful intent or purpose. Um...someone fired on me, and i gave my explaination. Sorry if your feeling that way.', 446, 464, 0, '2013-08-03 07:30:00'),
