(1575, 'If you''ve stripped the heads on the bolts, or rounded the nuts off, here are some things you can do:\r\n\r\n-- use a dremel with the cutting wheel to cut a new slot in the screw head, then use a slot screwdriver with that.\r\n\r\n--use channel locks on the rounded nuts, and then be careful with the screwdriver when you back the bolts out.\r\n\r\n--use the Dremel''s cutting wheel to cut off the bolts, just below the nut. You don''t have to cut right between the baseplate and nut (scarring the baseplate and likely breaking a few cutting wheels), but rather halfway up the side of the nut. After you cut off the top half, the bottom will come right out.\r\n\r\nWhen done, use brand-new skate hardware purchased from a skate shop, Home Depot, Lowes or Ace... and buy extra so you have spares.', 456, 184, 0, '2013-09-28 07:30:00'),
