(2201, 'I see someone here said that we shouldn''t shop by brands. Actually we should and on the other hand we should not. Why? Because most of the companies make their decks from different maple. See not every maple tree can be same, they are all trees but not all of them has same durabillity, thickness etc (same as humans, we are all made by organs and tissues, but not all of us are equally strong, resistant etc you know what I mean). Anayway, every brand has theirs different suppliers of maple layers from different wood industries. Some of them are good some are bad.\r\nBack on what i wanted to say. Someone here said that we shouldn''t shop by brand and that we should find something that fits our taste. Well mate, you are in one hand right in one hand wrong.\r\nEnjoi, Almost, Blind, Speed Demons are one same company, same wood suppliers, same factory produces those decks, ony thing different are shapes and board pictures. Also this works for Habitat and AWS, Mystery and Zero etc...\r\nSo there is NO MATTER either if the board is Sheckler pro model or Brian Wenning pro model, IT IS THE SAME WOOD.\r\n\r\nWHAT WE SHOULD BUY BY ARE THE SERIES!!! Older series - older wood, and we all know that wood lowers its quality in time, Newer series - fresher wood and has better quality.\r\n\r\nSo someone will buy some Plan B from an older series, and it will snap easy, and someone will buy a newest series of Blind decks and it will last a longer time. And then it becomes, Plan B''s are shit and Blind rules.\r\n\r\nSo you get what I mean, we should shop by brand, and on the other hand not. Just watch the series from each company.', 495, 731, 0, '2008-02-29 18:30:00'),
