(2486, 'Hey Everyone,\r\n\r\nThis is Jeff. I own Blank Skate. I used to post on here a while back.\r\n\r\nI''ve actually been so busy lately that it is hard to get on here and post as much as a I like. I was shocked to see how much this site has grown. It is really quite amazing.\r\n\r\nThe reason I have been so busy is because I have started my own woodshop. We are now manufacturing our decks right here in Pittsburgh using 100% USA Hardrock Maple and Non-Toxic Glues. What we do is a little different than what most people who sell "blank decks" do.\r\n\r\nWe actually take the time to make our boards and sell them direct. We do not buy factory seconds or chinese boards and label them our own. We take a lot of pride in what we do. Blank Skate is 100% Skater Owned and Operated.\r\n\r\nWe sponsor a team of 8 Skaters. We love 3rd Lair and thier Top Shop Competition. We''ve been there twice now taking home a 9th and a 5th Place out of all the shops in the country.\r\n\r\nWe do demos, product tosses, contests and charity work. We have just started our own magazine that is free to view online and will come out every two months.\r\n\r\nSome of the posts stated that "blanks" don''t give back to the skateboarding. And you may be shocked to find out that I actually believe that. I don''t belive in dumping mass quantities of imported skateboards into the market or dumping them on popular auction sites. That does not contribute anything to skateboarding. It only serves to line the pockets of those who do it.\r\n\r\nThat is exactly why we do things differently. We are a Manufacturer/Shop/Deck Company all in one. We give back way more than we take. (Just look at my financial records - ha ha)\r\n\r\nANy feedback you have or questions you may have for me, feel free to ask. I have always been very open about what we do and who we do it for.\r\n\r\nLater\r\nJeff Gorilla', 496, 930, 0, '2007-12-16 18:30:00'),
(2487, 'the skateboard that has lasted me the longest is a DSM Woodshop Resin-8 / 8-Ply Epoxy\r\nmade in China...\r\nI ride 8.25" and normally and I go through about a board every two to three weeks depending on how often and hard I skate... the tail lasts a lot longer than anythang else I''ve rode. it just keeps its pop for way longer... must be the epoxy they are aloud to use in China, just don''t try to eat it ''cuz you never know when it comes from China... try a DSM blank Resin-8 for your self... it is a great deck ...', 496, 931, 0, '2007-12-19 18:30:00'),
