(2489, 'Gorilla your post is too large to quote but yes that sounds awesome what you are doing. I would definetly support and get my hands on a board from you if I wasnt here in Australia. Blanks boards are good but there is a bout 100000(over exaggerated) blank companies. Some are good some arent. I support shop blanks and such but ebay is good if you dont have the money etc.', 496, 933, 0, '2007-12-31 18:30:00'),
(2490, 'Quote:\r\nOriginally Posted by Alfonso\nGorilla your post is too large to quote but yes that sounds awesome what you are doing. I would definetly support and get my hands on a board from you if I wasnt here in Australia. Blanks boards are good but there is a bout 100000(over exaggerated) blank companies. Some are good some arent. I support shop blanks and such but ebay is good if you dont have the money etc.\r\nEbay isnt good. It is a shame that we live in a country fuel by consumption driven by the desire to buy the cheapest possible product at the cheapest possible price. We just want it and want it cheap. We don''t care where it comes from or who we support in the purchase.\r\n\r\nI am sorry to hear that consumption patterns are the same in Austrialia.\r\n\r\nWhen you purchase based only on price, the costs start to far exceed the value.\r\n\r\nFor example:\r\nWho makes that product? Was it made in your country? Does it support your Economy?\r\nWhat is in the product? Chances are that the country it was made in does have the same working conditions or product standards as your own country.\r\n\r\nThe second point:\r\nYou can buy imported crap all day long that retails 40-70% below what it would have cost you to buy AMERICAN.\r\n\r\nI''ve bought so many thing thats were imported because they were cheaper. But I soon started to notice that they break, don''t hold up, or even damage something else. I bought those based on price, not purpose. If I would have bought the same product that was american made it may have cost me $10 more but would have lasted me 10 TIMES LONGER.\r\n\r\nWhen buy based on purpose it is actually CHEAPER and you CONSUME LESS. Make smart decisions. Maybe some items are more expensive, but they''ll last you a whole lot longer.\r\n\r\nBuy only what you need, not what you want.\r\n\r\nAlso, there really arent 100000 blank companies out there. There are a bunch of guys who buy chinese wood and factory seconds. And then there is Blank Skate who actually makes a 100% AMERICAN Made skateboard deck.\r\n\r\nOur Wood comes from the Great Lakes Region of the USA\r\nOur Glue comes from Ohio\r\nOur Sealants come from Pittsburgh PA.\r\n\r\nWe take alot of pride in that. We also end up selling our boards for less than many companies sell the chinese imports.\r\n\r\nLater\r\nJeff', 496, 930, 0, '2008-01-02 18:30:00'),
