(2959, 'You should get a Syder deck from Spyder Surf shop in Hermosa Beach, CA. The decks are great and have a lot of concave, I am skating my 3rd one and they are better than pro decks, they have a crap load of pop and they keep it (longer than deluxe boards) and they are durable and light. They are $30 with grip, and if you cant get one from the shop call them.2461 Pacific Coast Hwy, Hermosa Beach, CA 90254\r\n(310) 374-8276.\r\nThe decks are increible and it''s great to support local. THEY WILL SHIP ONE TO YOU FOR $45 OR LESS. BUY ONE, TRUST ME THEY ARE INCREDIBLE!!!! AND THEY HAVE A LOT OF CONCAVE AND POP', 508, 1110, 0, '2014-03-02 18:30:00'),
(2960, 'I finally retired my mini-logo K-12 and threw on a new Laugh I was "flowed" and so far my impressions are good.\r\n\r\nOne of the great things about Laugh skateboards is you can pick what type of concave you want, so there''s less of a mystery there. I told them I wanted one in "deep dish" and it is legitimately a steep concave.', 508, 448, 0, '2014-03-03 18:30:00'),
(2961, 'Any Real deck.', 508, 1111, 0, '2014-03-03 18:30:00'),
(2962, 'almost, enjoi, blind, darkstar (not from walmart, those are fake!), and any other brand from dsm have awesome pop cause they re individualy pressed. Other companys that still stack and press 5 directly on top of each other makes 5 different decks. Top has the most pop, bottom has the least pop. Thats why on reviews some complain that a deck has no pop wile another person would say it had amazing pop. When you order online, theirs preaty much a 1/5 chance youll get a deck withe the right amount of pop you like. :P', 508, 481, 0, '2014-03-03 18:30:00'),
(2963, 'From what I''ve ridden over the past few years:\r\n\r\nAnti-Hero\r\nDGK (Kayo)\r\n\r\nI prefer the shape of Anti-Hero over Kayo but love the feel of kayo wood and concave; I should buck up and get used to the tapered noses and tails.\r\n\r\nPPS (older presses before they switch so PSstix)', 508, 445, 0, '2014-03-03 18:30:00'),
