(2966, 'I know what you mean, I love super concave. There was a a pro model Pepe Martinez back in the day maybe 15-20 years ago that had the most concavity I have ever felt. The graphic on the bottom of the deck was of a mexican sleeping under a cactus wearing a sombrero. I broke it and have been looking for another ever since with no luck. I wish I could find another, I think it was a Capital deck.\r\n\r\nI have been using the monster steep concave listed above and it''s pretty decent, but still not the same as what I remember that pepe deck was.....', 508, 1112, 0, '2014-04-28 18:30:00'),
(2967, 'Another for Real. Not crazy but they are pretty steep on the sides.', 508, 277, 0, '2014-04-28 18:30:00'),
(2968, 'Yes they do, they are Kayo corp.\r\n\r\nThe tail however differs from DLX and etc......simply its better.\r\n\r\n\r\nBascially youll have to see but im saying you shoudnt be let down man. but the noses and tails differ a lot.\r\n\r\nBut my everyday friend damn near roommate is flow for Organika now and those boards are on point.\r\n\r\nSo get one id recommend. You will like them I bet. I skate Kayo corps, organika, dgk, exp, but like real too. But im sure you will enjoy your board so id recommend giving it a go.\r\n\r\nI love them more than the other boards posted. get a decent size noting under a 8 id recommend assuming your a Huuuuuge bitchhhh. but with a name like Hugo, you must be a big fellow.\r\n\r\noh shit, all that and I said not much...the concave is perfection. lots of it and THEY LAST.', 509, 279, 0, '2014-04-28 18:30:00'),
