(3049, 'Etnies Bastiens- Lasted awhile, toe cap ripped and there was the white rubber underlay which lasted awhile. The grip was good while it lasted, it like all faded within 2.5 weeks.\r\n\r\nDC Ryan Smiths- Awesome grip, it lasts soo long. Usually grip is gone with me in 3 weeksm and I have had these shoes for over a month and the grip is still really good. The toe cap gets all slippery but nothing bad. They have optional lace protection and the insoles are awesome. Big heel pad in it.\r\n\r\nES K7s- Dont buy them, they rip easy, and the grip actually went away in one spot in one session. Not even 2 weeks and I had holes in the bottom of my shoes, and in the heel a hole came and the G2 fell out after skating.', 517, 1128, 0, '2006-01-14 18:30:00'),
(3050, 'DC Lynx 2- Great shoe so far, had em for about a week and love em. The boardfeel is perfect for me, not to much(reynolds 3) but not too little either. Right in the middle. The super suede is super nice and flicks really nice. It seems fairly durable but I can''t tell the real durability after only having them for a week. These shoes also have lace loops for the first two laces, and then the rest of the laces are hidden. I doubt that I will ever rip laces with these shoes. The best part is that I got these for $35 from the active mailorder sale.\r\n\r\nI would definately recommend you to get this shoe, check out http://www.activemailorder.com/Catal...x=1&at=-1&bi=0 to get them.', 517, 849, 0, '2006-01-14 18:30:00'),
(3051, 'Adio Hamltons- Worst shoe ive had.Starting ripping First day I skated them.Grip didn''t last more then 2 weeks.Not very Comfy.\r\n\r\nVans Half-Cab- Pretty Comfy.Grip Lasted quite Nicely.Never ripped in the 2 months I had em.However The Rubber onround the Shoe fell off so They sended up looking like slippers.\r\n\r\nDVS Getz 2- Good Shoe.Very Comfy.Grip lasts So long.Rip easy though.The Heel Air Bag is quite nice.\r\n\r\nEtnies Atro Saari''s- crap.Grip don''t last at all.Very Very Comfy.Don''t rip too easly either.The Action Leather does chip easy though.Kinda bulky in my opinion.I didn''t like the board feel at all.\r\n\r\nEmerica Reynold 3- Great shoe.Grip lasts sooo long.Don''t rip easy.Shoe is very Flat though.Not very Comfy.Same thing Happened with these that happened to the Half-Cabs.\r\n\r\nCirca cx205:Terrible Shoe\r\n\r\nEmerica KSL:Rip Easy,Grip Wears down fast,Lace Guard don''t help.Board Feel is great.I liked them.\r\n\r\nEmerica Ellingtons- Even though they last really well, I Hated them. They were bulky and felt bad.\r\n\r\nFallen Cheifs- Rip fairly easy. Comfy. Grip lasts well. Good shoe.', 517, 1131, 0, '2006-01-14 18:30:00'),
(3052, 'Vans idk- these were my first skate shoes it was one of those u can get at a cheap price, the grip went very fast but it was ok i guess.\r\n\r\nAdio Bam V2- These were a mistake, its a good thing i got the leater kind, their ok when u first get them but after that their not so good, the air bag poped towrd the end of its life, and i didn''t go off anything that high.\r\n\r\nEs Accels- Great shoes! The grip lasted a long time, it griped great, nice padding, the boardfeel was just right, took impack well, over all one of the best i ever had. wouldn''t mind getting these again.\r\n\r\nEmerica Reynolds 3- These skate REALY good, the grip is soo good, the boardfeel is amazing, doesn''t take inpact well on the bottom of the ball of my foot, but u can feel the g2 which its ok but i haven''t done anything high on these yet, durribilty isn''t great but o well, if u can find these for cheap then get them.\r\n\r\nFallen Ace- don''t skate in these untill my Reynolds are gone, but the board feel is just about right and it feels good in my feet, ill have to skate it and get back to u on these.', 517, 1132, 0, '2006-01-14 18:30:00'),
