(3079, 'Globe Mojo Hi: It''s aight, but has terrible grip. It lasted about 2 weeks without shoo goo.\r\n\r\nSavier Sherman: Good luck finding this one, but if you do, buy it. Lasted 4 weeks and then a few more of on and off skating with a hot glue gun for patchwork. Great grip, great seamless toe, aight padding, and good board feel. Definitely a top pick.\r\n\r\nI-Path Grasshopper: Great shoe, but lasts about 2 weeks at most with shoe goo. Great board feel, aight toe area, not too much cushioning, but overall my favorite shoe ever.\r\n\r\nI-Path Bangera: Great shoe, hard to find. Great toe area, great padding, great board feel, not too great durability, lasts 2 to 3 weeks. Overall a top pick, but not so easy to find.\r\n\r\nI-Path Yogi Hi: Not my favorite I-Path, but my friend had his and loved them. Not too great on padding, boardfeel, or cushioning, but aight durability. Lasted 3 weeks, and not a top pick.\r\n\r\nI-Path Cricket: Basically a low-top Grasshopper, but for some reason they didn''t last as long or have as good break in time. Not such a good pick overall.\r\n\r\nDvs Prophet: It''s aight. Good board feel, good cushioning, aight durability, overall a solid pick, but not good enough for a perfectionist.\r\n\r\nNike Dunk Mid: Not a SB, but I really liked having more board feel and less cushioning. It was a great shoe and even better in SB.\r\n\r\nAdidas Torrent: Built like a tank. With a little shoe goo, these could last you about 2 months or about seven weeks, a world record for me. The only setback is that some of the foam near the rubber toecap begins to wear, but overall, a little shoe goo will fix that. The board feel is superior, but it does not have a high break in time. Has great cushioning and a nice rubber toe cap. Overall a great shoe, styled like a DC Lynx 2, but less tech and longer lasting.\r\n\r\nDC Lynx 2: Overall its aight. I would recommend it to mostly ledge skateboarders, because it just didn''t have enough cushioning for my bruised up feet. Excellent grip and board feel. The super suede is ok, but you still need shoe goo. Overall it''s ok, but it only lasts 3 weeks before the grip on the bottom goes out and all you have is your sock poking through.\r\n\r\nEs Accel Plus: It''s ok, a lot of people say that accels are where its at, but after a week of skateboarding the sole still didn''t break in. They are overall allright shoes if you get them in leather, but they didn''t break in to my standards in three weeks, and by that time, the sole pretty mush wore out from skateboarding every single second of the day because it was Thanksgiving break. Overall, not too great in my opinion, but if you like them, you like them.\r\n\r\nSavier Cooper: Not my favorite Savier, but excellent durability, it just seemed like it skated weird, and the grip was weirdin out. Overall it''s ok, but not too great.\r\n\r\nEs K4: I got them when I was young and niave, but they looked like an all black basketball shoe and to say the least, skated like one. They had great boardfeel, but the whole rounded rubber toe cap thing threw me off and the grip wore out in like 4 weeks, which nowadays would last about one week, so don''t buy them.\r\n\r\nEtnies Sal 23: Excellent shoe, especially with shoe goo. Great grip, great durability, great and minimal padding, but no cushioning, but it doesn''t matter. Great shoe to just put on and skate. Right now, these shoes have lasted about a month and I intend to wear them until the sole goes out, so I''m guessing they will last about five weeks top. Also, don''t shy away from these shoes because other punks label them as "poser shoes", because they are definitely one of the greatest shoes created.\r\n\r\nOverall I''d go with the Sal 23 if you''re into Accels, because they''re like them, but without the bulk. But If you have the money to get new shoes often, or you don''t go thru shoes too fast, get Grasshoppers.\r\n\r\nShoe Release Anticipated: Waiting on word about how those new Supras are gonna be and REALLY waiting for that new I-Path Locust. It looks like a Grasshopper with new grip so it will last longer, making it the best shoe ever.', 517, 1155, 0, '2006-01-21 18:30:00'),
