(3127, 'Arto Saari Etnies, Leather - Only get these shoes if they are the leather ones. The suede will rip on you so easy. I owned the leather Arto Etnies for a good 8 months and they havn''t ripped yet, only a little bit of marking on the front from doing tricks. After I owned them, I had given them to a friend, Freakn_Style, and he has used them for a couple of months, still havn''t ripped. These shoes have good grip and hug your foot for maximum comfort and flexibility.\r\nI would give these shoes an 11/10, and would recommend them to anyone looking for a nice, strong, durable shoe.', 517, 1200, 0, '2006-03-25 18:30:00'),
(3128, 'Globe Cash\r\nHehe, these shoes suck A LOT. I tried them on at the store, and they felt really comfortable. After less than a week of skateboarding, the stitching at the front got messed up. Two weeks and the shoes ripped completely. Unless you are just gonna walk around in them, DO NOT get these shoes.', 517, 502, 0, '2006-03-25 18:30:00'),
(3129, 'Etnies TheTIP\r\nOk, these shoes aren''t that bad. Definatly need more padding, but they arent really uncomfortable. If you are gonna get these shoes, only use them for skating because they are uncomfortable to just walk around in. They also REALLY suck for running. Now lets get to skating. The laces rip quickly, but they bring an extra pair. The stiching holds up well, and the shoe doesn''t rip. The last problem with the shoes is that the sole wears down easy, and eventually rips. I give these shoes a 7/10.', 517, 502, 0, '2006-03-25 18:30:00'),
