(3198, 'Es Accels - I love these shoes. By far the best Ive had. I really like the toe cap or whatever it is , it stays strong and doesnt rip to easily. They are amazingly comfortable. Not only this, but I personally HATE bulky or heavy shoes.\r\n\r\nEtnies Vallely - These shoes were pretty crappy to be honest. I have liked almost every shoe I have bought so Im not that picky. These shoes are really bulky, heavy, and strong. That is probably the only one good thing about these , they are strong.\r\n\r\nGlobe Rhythm - These are kind of old shoes and hard to find but I really like them. The one problem is they rip VERY easily.', 517, 1251, 0, '2006-06-07 18:30:00'),
(3199, 'Fallen Heritage - these shoes were sweet looking and i remember getting them at the start of my freshman year and wearing them until feburary or so. The sole wears really quick but i didn''t get a hole in the toe.\r\n\r\nemerica reynolds 2 - I would buy another pair of these but i can''t stand to rip laces all the time. They were great shoes and the toe only got one hole after 8 months. there was absolutely no grip left after 5 or 6 months though. zig zag grip just bites.\r\n\r\nemerica reynolds 3 - these aren''t that good, the toe glows out and the grip sole is very thin, but they do look cool. it lasts 2 months of everyday intermediate skating before it is completely blown out on the sides.\r\n\r\nes accel plus - the grip is better than most shoes, i''ve been skating in these since feburary and it is now june and the toe is torn and could be worse if i didn''t shoe goo it back together. the sole is flattened and seems to be detaching itself from the foam on the inside.\r\n\r\nAdio Wray v4 - these are pretty bad. I was just learning to kickflip and boardslide with them and I tore the toe to the point were i needed shoe goo in about a month and a half. The grip was completely gone and the laces tore like crazy.\r\n\r\netnies lo cut - these were so bunk that i would have rather skated bare footed. They hurt to walk in and felt like i was wearing a dress shoe. no shock absorbing, the toe rips so quick. I bought these and after two weeks of just wearing them i bought other shoes.\r\n\r\nemerica tilt - this shoe lasts forever, the grip doesn''t flatten quick, the toe doesn''t blow out and the laces stay on longer. My only problem is that they are very low on my ankles and there is practically no kind of foam/gel/airbag for the heel.', 517, 1252, 0, '2006-06-08 18:30:00'),
(3200, 'Emerica Heritic 2- 8/10.... decent shoe for a while. but if you make yours last 5 months they can get annoying\r\n\r\nFallen Rival Lo-Fi- I have only had these for a day but they are freakin incredible.... comfortable, good grip, a little heavy but that didnt affect me at all..... i skated these 4 hours today and one little stitch popped up but its nothing really... the strap is really good for protecting the tongue and keeping your shoes tight', 517, 1253, 0, '2006-06-10 18:30:00'),
(3201, 'ellingtons-great shoe rip a kinda quickly but still skateable\r\n\r\ntnt II-the best buy it', 517, 1139, 0, '2006-06-12 18:30:00'),
(3202, 'Circa 205- really comfortable while they last, but laces rip easily, sole wears out supper fast, toe cap wears out fast as well ( he ones w/ red bottoms get the red all over your griptape)\r\n\r\nHere are mine after a couple months', 517, 1254, 0, '2006-06-15 18:30:00'),
(3203, 'circa CX 404- horrible shoes i had this even when i sucked.... i had 2 holes in each shoe after 2 months the material ripped in about 2 weeks laces ripped in about 1 insoles are worn out right away and the only good thing is there a lil bit comfy but after insole is worn in they jus suck\r\n\r\nes accel plus-incredible comfort material lasted a long time grip lasted a long time this is a shoe i would recomend to every skater on this site\r\n\r\nes rodrigo tx-worst es shoe i ever had after i had my accels i was jus tottaly surprised after these only lasted as long as my circa''s but.. i learned my first kickflip in them.. they are very good for flip tricks and on the bottom there are holes to take the pressure but the durability killed it if these were more durable these would be like the new accels but they sucked\r\n\r\ndc avatar-1st pair of DC very comfy good for flip tricks pretty comfy, durable i would recomend these to many ppl\r\n\r\nes anti social-awesome shoes best durability ever grip is as good as accels maybe even better my heels have never hurt from these, these are definitly the new accels these are packed with good features i love these shoes and i recomend these TO EVERY SKATER IN THE WORLD!!!!!', 517, 1255, 0, '2006-06-17 18:30:00'),
