(3206, 'es accels- awesome shoes, they have great board feel, durability, and theyre really comfy 8/10\r\n\r\nfallen patriots- The only thing that I liked about these shoes was the look, they lasted kinda long too, they had almost no board feel and i hated the way they skated 6/10\r\n\r\nemerica reynolds 3- these skated so well, they were really cool looking too, but they ripped pretty fast 9/10\r\n\r\nsupra vulk low- im currently skating these and theyre great, ive had them for 3months and they are just starting to get a hole in them, they skate really well too. (only 40$ at skateparkoftampa) 8/10', 517, 1257, 0, '2006-06-19 18:30:00'),
(3207, 'DVS profile- I loved these........ i had them for a full year before they finally blew out. They were durable as hell, but the grip fell of faster than the sole, but they still skated great. 10/10\r\n\r\nAdio hamilton: Horrible. Board feel was shit and i got a hole in the toe cap first\r\nday of skating. The inside part near the heel tore open, so it always cut my heel. that hurt. looked cool though. 4/10\r\n\r\nLakai Howard 2: Quite possibly the worst shoe I''ve ever skated. First day of skating some of the grip completely faded away. Third day the toe cap tore open. within two months, they were so messed up I just gave them to my friend. 2/10', 517, 1258, 0, '2006-06-20 18:30:00'),
(3208, 'Airwalk-These are some crappy off brand along with NSS that just sucks. My friend can only popshovit and completely ripped apart two pairs of shoes in 3 months.\r\n\r\nCircaCX105 - I could wear these golfing they''re so ugly. They dont have tongue straps or lace gaurds and the grip is slippery with no padding. Tough leather though.\r\n\r\nVans TNT II - These shoes are some of the best looking out there, the sole extremely thin but it''s vans classic grip, the insole liner is super thick. Durability seems alright, and the shoe is very comfy\r\n\r\nDVS revival - These are ugly, too basic, but the toe is strong and the side panel is strong. The grip is awful, it tears off so quick. no lace protection\r\n\r\nEs Rodrigo TX - the grip on these shoes is incredible, the lace protectors are great and the shoe overall holds up very well.\r\n\r\nFallen Ace - these are pretty good. tough grip and suede upper. a slimmer shoe with good board feel.\r\n\r\nVans Estillo - this shoe does not last very long, it''s cool for a month, but then is dead. Grip is too soft and leather is very weak.\r\n\r\nVans old skool (and slip on) - these thin vans should only be worn by pool skaters or vert dogs, they are not good for street skating. If you don''t do any flip tricks, or just don''t do anything that requires an ollie, then these shoes are good for you. They''re more for casual style anyways', 517, 1252, 0, '2006-06-25 18:30:00'),
(3209, 'DVS Revival (Splat)- Comfortable shoe after you break them in. The toe rips pretty easily. Laces rip fast, just a basic, simple skate shoe. I''ve had them for about two months, but I have been skating these and another pair of Emericas at the same time, swapping out every few days. I''d buy them if they were on sale and you needed a quick shoe, because that''s what I did.. 5/10\r\n\r\nEmerica Heretic 2- I got these from a regular footed friend, and I''m goofy, they had been slightly used. Very comfortable, didn''t require much breaking in, but that could just be due to the fact that they were used when I got them. The toe stiching ripped pretty quickly. The grip lasts quite a while before ollie holes start to form. Laces don''t rip too quick... 7/10', 517, 1259, 0, '2006-06-27 18:30:00'),
(3210, 'Why do people call reynolds 3 shit?\r\n\r\nI only really skate ledges below my waist by the way.\r\n\r\nEDIT:\r\n\r\nNever mind I got No Skools 20% off. I havn''t got to skate in them properly (I only had a 10 minute roll-a-round)', 517, 1190, 0, '2006-06-28 18:30:00'),
