(3226, 'fallen heritage: a good shoe, looks nice. they held up for me nicely. the soles lasted for about two months. the toe cap ripped before this, but it was easy enough to fix with shoe goo.\r\n\r\nemerica canal: i''m sure it''s out of production, but it was a decent shoe. the toe did not rip at all, instead it became discolored. the soles only lasted a month or so.\r\n\r\nemerica miner: i believe this is also out of production now, but.. excellent ankle support. strong suede, the toe didn''t rip for quite awhile. soles were durable.\r\n\r\nemerica francis: great shoe so far. the ankle support is brilliant, and the soles have held up. i''ll update this later.', 517, 1269, 0, '2006-07-23 18:30:00'),
(3227, 'Adio Wray V4: CRRRAAAAPPPPPP grip last about a month, laces rip SOOO Easy, toe cap rip in about 2 skates Over All 5/10\r\n\r\nGlobe Focus: They''re Alright. Lasted About 3 Months. Good Shoe Not The best. 7/10\r\n\r\neS Accelerates: GREAT Shoe lasted Me About 8 Months two problems I had Were The Laces Ripped Quite Easely And The G2 startd To Waer Out And Go Flat So You''d Feel ALL The Impact 9/10\r\n\r\nOsiris Troma: New Shoes. Heaps Good; Cheap (Only 100 Aus) Great Fell So Far. Just A Bit To Low 10/10', 517, 628, 0, '2006-07-23 18:30:00'),
(3228, 'Adio Kenny anderson V1- great shoe. Ive had them for a year and i skate them every day. so comfy. not the best board feel and a little ripping at the "A" logo. Little wear at the toe on the sole.\r\n\r\nAdio Hammilton- WORST SHOE EVER. rips sooooooo easy. sole wore so fast and toe ripped soooooooooooo fast crappy board feel\r\n\r\nEtnies Sheckler- Had them for 5 months and there amazing there great for skateing. exelent board feel. but suade rips after about a monyh of skateing\r\n\r\nVans Estello- amazing shoe so good board feel and amazing durability.', 517, 1270, 0, '2006-07-23 18:30:00'),
(3229, 'DC Smith- I got these in the leather. Skate like shit right out of the box, but if you break them in they skate much better. Really tight at first, but this goes away.\r\n\r\nAs far as durability goes, these things are a tank. It''s got a plastic toe cap, Meaning it doesn''t rip anytime soon (Mine still haven''t ripped). Comes with lace protection, but the stitching on that breaks fairly easy. Laces are pathetic- after a few 360 flips, my laces ripped in two different areas. That was the only thing I didn''t like.\r\n\r\nFor comfort, it''s like I said- Tight as hell at first, but that goes away as you wear them. It''s got a huge gel insert in the heel, which helps tremendouly. Too bad there''s no coushining for the footbed- anything higher than a five set hurts a little. Watch out for that.\r\n\r\nGrip is pretty good. Most of mine''s still there, and usually it''d be gone by now (4 months). Board feel was pretty good- Not too much like the reynolds 3, but not too little like the rival lo-fi.\r\n\r\nOverall, I''d Recommend them. They''re durable, have good grip and are pretty comfy (what more could you want?) 9/10', 517, 1258, 0, '2006-07-24 18:30:00'),
(3230, 'fallen rival lo-fi - a m a z i n g. theyve lasted so much longer than my fallen patriots. the first day i skated them they were scuffed aft er 30 minutes from doing flip tricks, but im just now starting to get those little V''s. so they just scuff easy, but the shoe is amazing. very very comfortable. good support and grip. theyre starting to wear out cause ive had them a good 3 months. i know im sticking with fallen forever. i love them. anyone got a good recomindation for my next shoe? im thinking of getting the troopers or ace. any help?', 517, 1271, 0, '2006-07-24 18:30:00'),
