(3271, 'I think I''ve posted things about some of these before, but I don''t really remember.\r\n\r\nDVS Revival- Grip didn''t last very long. It was okay, but nothing to really brag about. Super great board feel. It wasn''t too durable, though. Great shoes to buy if you can find them on sale or something. I''d give them a 6.5/10. They''re probably worth $40-$50 at most. I loved skating them, though. I could usually get all of my flip tricks with them, even after the toe had basically ripped completely off.\r\n\r\nCirca CX205-I''m still skating these shoes, along with my Es Accels. I''ll alternate, so I''ve basically been skating these things three days a week for about a month or so. They still haven''t ripped at all, and the grip is still there completly. I''ve heard that the leather ones suck, though, So stay away from those. But they''re pretty much one of my favorite shoes. Some people say that they suck, but I don''t know why. I love them so far.\r\nThey''re really comfy after you break them in, too. They have some sort of padding in the sole, so the impact resitance is great, without sacrificing too much board feel. Worth the origional price. 8/10.\r\n\r\nEs Accel- I haven''t skated these very long, so I won''t write too much about them.\r\nGrip lasts forever. No sign of it giving up anytime soon. Great board feel, the shoe is decent. But it rips faster than anything I''ve ever skated before. I mean, it''s really bad, the toe ripped the first day I skated it. But like most shoes, people say the leather ones suck. And I''ve got the leather ones. So go figure.', 517, 1259, 0, '2006-09-01 18:30:00'),
