(3297, 'Vans Estilo - Skate surprisingly good. Felt broken-in in the first session. Super flexible soles. Full waffle grip. The insoles have a nice rubber thing where the heel is that somehow makes me feel more protected from heel bruises. Board feel is great for a cupsole shoe. Tongue starts out puffy and tends to mash in.\r\n\r\nOsiris Hsu 2 - Decent. Grip isnt so great but theyre nice and thin which helps you feel your board. toecap doesnt last for shit (nothing under it but stitching). Has some impact cushioning in the insoles. I got''em for 20 bucks which is okay, but I wouldn''t pay more than that.\r\n\r\nLakai Frazier - A bit too stiff and the soles dont last at all and the toe cap is only double stitched. They do have a plastic layer under the toecap though which helps. The straps saved my ankles numerous times. The laces seem to sit up higher on the shoe, so I didn''t tear any laces skating them, just the soles. The strap is also removable if you''re not into straps.\r\n\r\nDC Atlas (one of Rob Dyrdek''s shoes) - I had''em in leather. They don''t skate so great but they last unbelieavably long. They have like running shoe grip which takes FOREVER to wear down. They''re nice and light and I''ve used''em to go running a few times. They have decent lace protectors as well and the toe area is nice and narrow which helps your flick. The toe cap didnt tear for me, but I got them in green leather (weird), which just turned funky colors in the kickflip area but never tore.\r\n\r\nDC Avenger (AVE''s last pro model with DC) - They sucked. They''re ugly, I had a tear in the toe cap within my first session of skating them. They''re hard to break in, and they''re hella stiff. Fuck these shoes. I only got''em cause they were 20 bucks at Ross.', 517, 1307, 0, '2006-11-22 18:30:00'),
