(3301, 'Es Accelerates- Wonderful, i got the Black suede/gum sole, and i dont know why everyone complains about the sole coming off, mines fine i got it late this summer, it rips a little fast, and after your ollie guard dies, dont expect more than 10 minutes with a shoelace without the hidden protection. Even While ripped they still have amazing flick, unlike the leather ones which become completely smooth. Get them.\r\n\r\nDVS Revival Series - it SUCKS, amazingly comfortable, but the shoe completely died in about a week, i dont think they are meant for skating, my normal kicking foot came through the shoe in a week and a half\r\n\r\nEs Accel - Pretty good, i think they look ill, but the accelerates are better because of the hidden lace, and they last a little longer\r\n\r\nEs Accel Plus- Only good in leather, they are almost indestructible, the varial heel section does die pretty fast, but the kickflip place does not wear easily, but towards the end of use, they become smooth and its impossible to get height on kickflips.', 517, 1309, 0, '2006-11-26 18:30:00'),
