(3309, 'Havent seen to many reviews on Lakai so let me toss one in....\r\n\r\nLakai Carroll 4- GREAT Shoe!! Best shoe I have owned in a long while. Awesome grip, snug fit. Laces stayed in good condition for a long time. Not the most comfortable shoe but very durable. The sides didn''t wear out on me for a long long time. I would highly suggest them as a dependable shoe.\r\n\r\ne''S Accelerate- Probably the most comfortable shoe I have ever owned, but these shoes got tore up pretty quick. Grip didnt last long, laces didnt last long, stitching on the side blew out like a flat tire. Very loose fit.\r\n\r\nDVS Berra 4- Not a bad shoe. Snug fit, nice grip. Again not very comfortable but pretty hardy. The toe was the first thing to go out on em''.\r\n\r\nCirca 205''s- Stylish shoe, but not for the hardcore skater. Nice grip, and the ankle strap was nice, but the sides/laces tore up really fast.\r\n\r\ne''S Anit-Social- Very comfortable and loose fit, but like the Accelerate, fell apart pretty quick.\r\n\r\nAll-n-all I would suggest Lakai as a good shoes. Just my two cents.', 517, 1315, 0, '2006-12-26 18:30:00'),
