(3318, 'globe mullens tensor edition\r\n\r\npros\r\nSUPER comfortable\r\nlots of foot support\r\ngood looking, if you like the style\r\ngood material for tricks\r\n\r\ncons\r\nno boardfeel because they are so comfortable\r\nno lace protection\r\nbad looking, if you don''t like the style\r\nleast durable shoe in the universe\r\n\r\ni had these shoes when i was somewhat of a beginner. i mostly did ollies and kickflips in them. within about 3 weeks they were long gone. the toecap was so split that it hurt my toes to skate in them. because i did not know what shoe goo was (although i don''t know if it even would have helped), i duck taped them, which helped them last another week. by then, other parts of the shoe started to rip, and so did my switch foot (i didn''t even skate switch). the tape ripped through, and the bottom soles were smooth as ice. it''s not like i skated everyday either, it was the beginning of school so i mostly only skated on weekends.\r\n\r\nthese shoes are not worth it for skateing unless you buy a new pair of shoes every two weeks or you just walk around in them.', 517, 894, 0, '2007-01-06 18:30:00'),
