(3364, 'Emerica: The Boss\r\naka Reynolds 4\r\n\r\nShoe: Very padded, not to greatest color ways, very snug fit, extremely padded, which can be good or bad.\r\n\r\nPros: G202 Gel System Airbag, Optional protective lacing system. padded. very absorbent to the shock off high docks and steps. Mesh padded Tongue.\r\n\r\nCons: Board feel is not good at all, grip, too grippy in my opinion. Toe cap was gone soon enough, some of the color way''s shape''s aren''t very lovely . Toe is weak after 2 months, hurts toes on kick-flips or anything you use your flick foot for on the toe area.\r\n\r\nOver all:\r\nBoard feel--2/10\r\nGrip--4/10\r\nPadding--11/10\r\nAbsorbent--8/10\r\n\r\nOverall Summary: Good shoe to take off big things, not best for anything like freestyle or street, but great padding, and comfort. Actually, to great padding.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nNew Review To Come: Lakai Kost-One', 517, 1345, 0, '2007-04-15 18:30:00'),
