(3370, 'eS Accel Plus:\r\n\r\nPros:\r\nReal comfy thanks to the g2 in the heel & ball of the shoe, & Sti Lv 2 insole,\r\nLook good,\r\nGood board feel once broken in which takes from 1 - 3 days,\r\nThe strap keeps your shoe on nice n firm & if u cant be arsed to tie your laces u can just strap up instead,\r\nGood grip,\r\nLasts a good few months.\r\n\r\nCons:\r\nThey dont make them anymore (sob!),\r\nFeel slightly chunkier than Accels because of the g2,\r\nThe last colourways they did b4 they stopped making them were terrible!\r\n\r\n\r\nIf u liked Accels but need a bit of extra padding then the Plus'' are your shoe. The slightly chunkier sole isnt that much of a problem as soon as u wear them in. Youll probably only notice the difference if you''ve skated Accels b4 the Plus''. I cant really comment on the toe box areas'' durability as I dont scrape my foot like I used to due to my ankles being fucked from yrs of skating so they dont bend/flex anymore.\r\neS seem to be getting rid of their Accel mod shoes. They''ve discontinued the Plus & it seems the Accelerate has disappeared from their website too, which is probably because they looked too similar to Accels but with a higher price tag due to the g2 combinations. I dont know why they didnt just continue to make the Plus''/Accelerates in maybe 1 or 2 simple colours instead of throwing out loads of wacky colours which arent gonna sell. Maybe they should revamp the Accel with a g2 but without the strap? Wishful thinking eh?!\r\nThe Accel Plus is 1 of the best shoes I''ve skated in the last 6 yrs.', 517, 1349, 0, '2007-06-03 18:30:00'),
(3371, 'I''ve skated tons...\r\n\r\nAdio Wray v4... not very good at all, grip and leather upper wears off quickly. I was really new to skating when I wore them and they tore quicly. comfy though\r\n\r\nEmerica Reynolds 2 - a good all around shoe, the only bad thing was no lace protection\r\n\r\nFallen Rival - a good shoe, I''m wearing them at the moment doing 360 flips, nollie flips, general all around skating and they are comfy and all around durable\r\n\r\nEmerica Reynolds 3 - The sole is too thin, my friend wore these and had to put another insole out of his old shoe in to cushion his feet. They rip very quickly\r\n\r\nFallen Ripper - these are good vulcanized shoes, the cushioning is not that great, but they are perfect shoes for mellow skating.\r\n\r\nVans Rowley Square - the stitching rips quickly but the shoe skates so darn good. I like slim shoes and prefer a cupsole so these are just perfect, just shoe goo the stitching before you skate them. The cushioning could be improved though super grippy outsole\r\n\r\nVans TNT II - My friend wears these and I would have bought them if they weren''t so low on the ankle. They have great board feel, the sole is a thick gelly stuff for comfort and cushion, but the ankle is just too low for my comfort\r\n\r\nEtnies - If you want etnies, get artos, shecklers, or ali''s because everything else rips up quickly. The facto or whatever is okay too.\r\n\r\nFallen Ace - It might be impossible to bruise your heel is this shoe, It has great heel cushion and good all over foot cushion. It is durable all around, I just think it''s the ugliest of all Fallens\r\n\r\nEs Accel Plus - This shoe is alright, I would buy more if the grip didn''t fade so quickly, They will last you about 2 to three months of average skating, but if you do flip tricks like crazy (P.J. Ladd) you may want extra pairs of this shoe. They are super comfy though.\r\n\r\nEs Square One - If I were pro and got shoes free, I''d definitely wear this, but seeing as how I don''t feel like buying a new pair of shoes every few weeks.', 517, 1350, 0, '2007-06-07 18:30:00'),
