(3375, 'Emerica Tilts are an unbelievably durable shoe but you better get some dr. scholls gel insoles cause they have a terribly thin insole. If you don''t skate anything bigger than 6 sets you would definitely love these. NOT THE TILT 2 OR THE FELT just the plain, old school tilt. If you buy Dr. Scholl''s insoles either the massage gel or sport gel inserts then these would be a comfy, great pair of shoes. The grip is INCREDIBLE, any emerica shoe with that triangle pattern has the best grip. The toe cap is amazing and they''re just okay around the ankle area. Like I said, I recommend these shoes to anyone skating smaller drops or mellow tech tricks.\r\n\r\nMost all of emerica''s shoes are great, with the exception of the reynolds 3, leo, and francis. The thin, and i mean thin vulk soles do nothing for my feet but grip like a charm. Go for B. Hermans, Ellington (if you find them), AR 2''s or the Boss (which is heavier but super strong and comfy), or the kircharts.', 517, 1350, 0, '2007-06-12 18:30:00'),
