(3396, 'Dvs Berra 3 - Don''t last long at all but I thought they were really good. (I ripped through the toe cap and had the grip hanging off in literally a week and a half\r\n\r\neS K7 - Also amazing shoes but fall apart quickly.\r\n\r\nEmerica The Boss - Amazing shoes but the grip wears quickly and they''re bulky and as well don''t have amazing boardfeel but good shoes.\r\n\r\nEmerica SDK Kirchart - Amazing shoes, gel in the heel and rubber toe cap also sexy looking and perform amazing no matter how you skate, perfect balance of protection and boardfeel.\r\n\r\neS Accel Plus - Awesome shoes but on the thin side with perfect everything.\r\n\r\neS Accel - Last along time the grip wore away eventually but I never got through the toe cap.\r\n\r\neS Accelerate - Horrible shoes, okay board feel but the gel in the heel will make a bubble and fuck up the grip.\r\n\r\nFallen Ranger - Really good shoes but they are pure vulc so don''t expect any mercy protection wise.', 517, 1365, 0, '2007-08-29 18:30:00'),
(3397, 'Adio Kenny Anderson V2\r\n\r\nLemme say this is an AMAZING shoe!\r\n\r\nGreat soles, grip last awhile, and it takes a while to rip. It took me about 2 months to get a noticable rip and this was when all I could do was regular. No switch at all, and no heelflip moves. 3 months and counting. The grip is starting to wear though. Also it takes awhile to get used to em.', 517, 1366, 0, '2007-09-21 18:30:00'),
(3398, 'Emerica Reynolds 3\r\n\r\nBoard Feel: The board feel on these shoes are great! It''s one of the better shoes I''ve skated.\r\nScore: 8.5 / 10\r\n\r\nDurability: I''ll admit these shoes are great, but the durability is crap. I skated in them for a week and they ripped up. Not to mention the sole is/almost completely gone. The laces aren''t very durable and you''ll find yourself replacing laces every other session. My pair is retarded because I don''t skate switch or goofy and yet my right shoe got torn up.\r\nScore: 3 / 10\r\n\r\nGrip: The grip was pretty good. Even though my shoes are torn up I still have pretty great grip and that''s really all that matters to me I guess.\r\nScore: 8.5 / 10\r\n\r\nComfort: These shoes are somewhat comfortable regardless of the durability. I don''t recommend washing these shoes if you don''t have to (my pair got extremely covered in mud) because the gel on the insoles will come off. These shoes also seem to run a little big because I wear a 10.5 (well 11 now) but the owner of my local shop told me this and when I tried on a 10 (he was sold out of my size) they fit with extra room. So that could be a plus in someone''s case.\r\nScore: 7 / 10\r\n\r\nOverall Score: 6.75 / 10\r\n\r\nComments: I actually like this shoe but the durability is what kills it. I''d recommend buying these on sale or waiting for a price drop. I have a pair coming in February of next year that I got for $20 from CCS so I mean for that price I wasn''t (or couldn''t) refuse.', 517, 1367, 0, '2007-09-29 18:30:00'),
