(3417, 'Es Accels - Very good shoe. A little on the bulky side for those used to vulcanized shoes, but they had amazing board feel and durability. The soles last really long too. They have a rubber toe cap underneath the suede/leather toe cap for added durabillity as well as hidden lace loops.\r\n\r\nDVS Getz 2 - probably my favorite pair of shoes I ever owned. They were very comfortable and had great grip and had the perfect shaped toe cap for flip tricks. Didn''t last so long on the downside, they were pretty expensive too when I bought them.\r\n\r\nAdio Kenny Anderson V2 - Like a tank! These shoes last forever, however they dont have the greatest board feel. Very comfortable. I''d get them if you need a shoe that will last forever.\r\n\r\nAdio Jeremy Wray V4 - Not a fan... they are way too bulky to skate in. Used them for like a week and then couldn''t stand them any more...\r\n\r\nAdio Impact - Similar to the Kenny V2''s very durable, just very little board feel. They are cheap, like $50 worth getting if you need a pair that will last a long time.\r\n\r\nVans No Skool - Have great grip, long lasting sole and the toe cap has no stitchings that will rip, so it lasts fairly long. Very good board feel.\r\n\r\nDC Moses - Second greatest shoes I ever owned. The durability was lousy but the shoe had amazing grip and was very very light. Really nice boardfeel as well. If you can find a pair... go for it.\r\n\r\nIf I remember any other shoes I owned I''ll edit. Alot of these shoes are from about a year and a half ago so I don''t know if you can still find them.', 517, 1378, 0, '2007-11-01 18:30:00'),
