(3419, 'Lakai Howard Selects: Great vulcanized shoe with nice boardfeel. The grip is good while it lasts. It is kinda thin so the durability is about the same as any other vulcanized shoe. The insole is thick so it won''t hurt your feet that much unless you like to jump ledges and stairs. Takes a few days to get used to and break them in completely. Fairly cheap as well.\r\n\r\nEs Accelerates: Longest lasting shoe I ever had so far. Very comfy and looks clean (I got the green/black colorway). Grip lasts forever and is durable as well (Even though many people say that the soles fall off of the accelerates, mine did not). The boardfeel is average. The only problem with this shoe is it looks kind of bulky. Get the green/black colorway cuz they don''t make em no more and all the other colorways seem to have sole problems.', 517, 1379, 0, '2007-11-03 18:30:00'),
