(3437, 'Etnies Sheckler 1: Pretty decent, good comfort, nice grip, rip very easily though!\r\nAdidas Gazelle Skate: Very good shoe, nice grip but the sole really wears away quickly (doesn''t matter though, it stays grippy). Lace protection works pretty good, and they don''t rip that fast. VERY good boardfeel.\r\nAdidas Stan Smith skate: Better looks than the gazelle imo, pretty much the same specs otherwise.\r\n\r\nI''ve taken a look in my shoe collection, and I''ve noticed that all of my older shoes (Vans, DS, DVS) have lace loops, and almost NONE of the recent shoemodels (any brand) have those. They saved me tons of laces in the past, I think it''s very strange that the shoebrands have removed those...', 517, 1391, 0, '2007-12-18 18:30:00'),
