(3441, 'fallen ace-have a narrowtoe cap, and it may feel weird at first, but it starts feeling really good. it has an amazing durability, and they have good shock absorbtion\r\n\r\n\r\ndc lynx 2- amazing shoe, lasts roughly 3-4 months, great flick on this shoe, i dont know why but it does. the grip wears down a little fast, but this shoe has amazing shock absorbtion. they look good to. 9/10\r\n\r\n\r\ndvs getz 1-this shoe alot probably havent seen. i was lucky and found it burried in a clearence box. these shoes are like cement bricks straight out of the box, but give them a week, and theyre as loose as your mom. they are pretty bulky with this really strong plastic under the toe cap, i wore through the sole before i even ripped the entire shoe, i found switch flips killed the shoe for some reason. 7/10\r\n\r\n\r\nthe fallen sting- this shoe has everything the ace has, but durability (i guess because of the shell cap?) but i found the sole of the shoe wears down slower than most shoes. 8/10\r\n\r\n\r\nksl 1-this shoe was amzing, it was durable, and had great feel, but i cant say much about the grip becuase i wore it all down in track,\r\n7/10\r\n\r\n\r\nadio jw v.4-this shoe was stiff at first, but it breaks in. this shoe lasted me 5 months, and the sole never seemed to wear down, the shock absorbtion was fairly good, but its a little do bulky for me to skate in. 7/10\r\n\r\n\r\nemerica crass- crappy shoe, horible feel last about 1 months, the sole is at your socks by that time to. 4/10\r\n\r\n\r\nfallen patriot-wonder shoe, this shoe has great feel, lasts about 5 months (with some duct tape) and 5 foot ledges feel like curbs with them. shock absorbtion is amazing!\r\n9/10', 517, 1395, 0, '2008-01-12 18:30:00'),
