(3450, 'Circa Peacemakers: I only got them because they were $15 and I NEEDED shoes. Total crap, synth leather ripped like hell in a week, grip was gone in about 3 days, and totally uncomfortable. The toe cap was 1/2 the width of the rest of the shoe so it hurt pretty bad to wear.\r\n\r\nSupra DoubleE''s: Fairly bulky shoe, but felt very nice to skate in. VERY comfortable. There''s STILL grip, even after I''ve blown out the toe entirely. I mean there aren''t anyy flat spots in the grip. Good shoe overall, but if you get it, get it in SUEDE. I got premium leather(that''s all they had for $20) and it pretty much destroyed itself.\r\n\r\nFallen Rippers: Probably my favorite shoes. The suede rips a little easy, but there''s so many layers that you won''t notice. Grip lasted about 3-4 weeks, now its totally gone. Be careful getting these if you don''t have wide feet though, because these shoes get about 2 times as wide as when you buy them. Great shoe overall.\r\n\r\nFallen Rising Sun: Most people say these rip, they probably buy the leather. I only skate suede now. Anyway, these are lasting just like the Rippers so far. It''s been a month, and they''re great. I get back to you on them\r\n\r\nEtnies Arto 2: Pretty thin shoes, G2 in the heel helps a lottt though. VERY grippy, comes at a price though. Seems like it''s wearing down pretty fast though. Not happy about that. Great shoe so far.\r\n\r\nLakai Soca: Absolute crap. End it there. Just don''t buy them.\r\n\r\nEmerica Heretic 1: Also crap. Used them before I could even kickflip, but heelflips destroyed them in less then a month. Holes in the bottom too.\r\n\r\nGlobe Appleyard 1: Great shoe, nice and cushy feel. Mine were a size too big though so I can''t really say much. They were really comfy and lasted about a month and a half.\r\n\r\nANYONE HAD THE SUPRA SUPRANO''S?', 517, 1402, 0, '2008-02-27 18:30:00'),
