(3461, 'Vans No Skool''s:\r\n\r\nComfort: 8/10 - The average skate shoe, lots of tongue padding and ankel padding is average\r\n\r\nGrip: 6/10 - They are pretty grippy with that waffle sole, the only bad thing is that it wears down hella fast, took about a month to have my toe part of the sole flattened\r\n\r\nPadding: 7/10 - Not too thin, but yet not too thick. they are fine for drops, your feet will only get hurt if doing say a average size 8 and above.. at the 8 set, you will just notice your feet stinging a tiny bit.\r\n\r\ndurability: 6/10 - The ollie area rips hella fast. I had a hole in my ollie area so you can see my sock before the toe cap faded a little more than noticeable. The Laces rip pretty easily, since theres no lace protection. The heelflip area is great though, it takes a while to tear.\r\n\r\nboardfeel: 9/10 - This is my favorite part of the shoes. The boardfeel is good enough so that you don''t hurt your feet, but you can feel the board perfectly. You wont hurt your feet on drops under about an 8 set, and you wont need to be searching for the edges of that board under your feet.\r\n\r\nOverall, I give this shoe an 8/10. The flick and everything is awesome, but they wear down just a little too fast for my liking.', 517, 1369, 0, '2008-03-31 18:30:00'),
