(3484, 'Nike SB zoom tre\r\n\r\n\r\nI have the green/brown ones. they were at my local skateshop, and that was the only color they had that was in my size. i also have the yellow/blue ones that i bought off of my friend for 30. very good price.\r\n\r\nComfort-most of the cushion is in the tounge, but there is still a lot of padding everywhere else. there is so much padding though. and the sole is fucking sick. after two weeks of wearing them, the sole is just so squishy. 9/10\r\n\r\ngrip-AWESOME. even after a few months of skating, it has only worn down slightly. its really easy to catch and do tricks, because the whole toe of the shoe is mesh, so it grips easily for flicks. its like a vulcanized shoe. 10/10\r\n\r\ndurability-AWESOME. ive been skating mine since MARCH. its september and im still usin them. its just great. the mesh, wears down, but it just never tears. and the laces never tear either because their on the inside, so it wont.\r\n\r\nboardfeel-its so so. theres so much padding that its somewhat hard to feel the board 7/10\r\n\r\nlooks-at first i thought it was the ugliest damn shoe ever, but when i saw them in real life, theyre pretty cool. it kinda has a basketball look. 8/10\r\n\r\nprice-not so good. i bought mine for 107 i think? but its definetly worth it because these shoes just last forever.', 517, 1425, 0, '2008-10-25 18:30:00'),
