(3527, 'Adidas Doleys- 9/10\r\nGreat shoe, shoe has great feel, iv been skating them so far for the past 2 months and doing good no rips just some wear and tear. im going to say a good lasting shoe\r\n\r\n\r\nemerica laced-10/10\r\ngreat shoe best feel ever, its a rip off from vans authenics but i think vans rip within an hour. but this shoe last way long its the vans to skate in that last a while too.\r\n\r\nvans old skool\r\n9.5/10\r\ngreat shoe lots of feel also, thin but has an ollie pad for it last a little longer. and looks great.\r\n\r\npretty much the best shoes iv skated.', 517, 1450, 0, '2009-04-29 18:30:00'),
(3528, 'Vans Half Cab Pros: These shoes are nice and grippy the flick is good and they lasted me for 2 and a half months\r\n\r\n\r\nVans AV Sk8 low: Great boardfeel I am currently skating them right now\r\n\r\n\r\nAdio Shauwn White v1: These are great shoes lasted me 3 months', 517, 1451, 0, '2009-04-29 18:30:00'),
(3529, 'es accel climate comtrol-\r\n\r\npros - grippy, but not too much grip, durable, if you rip it up alot its barely noticable from about 2+ feet away.\r\n\r\ncons - sole loses grip after a while\r\n\r\noverall 9/10', 517, 1452, 0, '2009-05-15 18:30:00'),
(3530, 'Osiris Bronx- Horrible boardfeel, you might as well be barefoot, my feet hurt after riding in these. Otherwise comfy when you''re not riding. When you straight lace them the tongue on them gets a little goofy and bends, so these shoes come off when you try the simplest of fliptricks. Really bulky, in a bad way. 4/10', 517, 1453, 0, '2009-05-16 18:30:00'),
(3531, 'Fallen Patriots-Lasted me for 4 months, good shoes but suede eventually totally ripped out. Laces would break in literally a day. All around good shoes though\r\n\r\nEmerica Reynolds Lights-Amazing shoes. Laces that they came with did not break easily, grip was really sticky, and flick was awesome. Didn''t like the look too much but these shoes were light as hell.\r\n\r\nEs Theory 1.5-Awesome shoes. Everything about these is good. They have the g2, sti level 1, a really well-hidden huge tongue stash pocket, sick laces, and grippy soles. Pretty durable as well, with shoe goo they will last a long time. Get the grey-purple color way the strap makes it look awesome.\r\n\r\nEmerica Hsus-Not good shoes. They run big too. But, the optional lace protection is crap and doesn''t work, and there''s absolutely no protection. The maroon ones that i got look awesome so I just wear em when im not skating.', 517, 1454, 0, '2009-05-20 18:30:00');
INSERT INTO `responses` (`id`, `content`, `postid`, `userid`, `havemedia`, `response_timestamp`) VALUES
(3532, 'Lakai Telford- Pretty good overall, nice boardfeel for a cupsole. not bad but not great impact support IMO. toe cap fell off after about 3 1/2 months of skating. rubber under the suede. good ankle support.\r\n\r\nNike sb p-rod 2 valentines- Great impact support, so comfy, a little too bulky for me. I learned a lot of tricks in these. Weak-ish ollie area. lasted for about 2 months and can still be repaired. good flick and good grip but got completely smooth. somewhat durable.\r\n\r\nEmerica Leos-Whack as hell, too thin, i got pain off a four stair, not durable at all, ollie area hole after 2 days, and grip flattened after a week. more for chilling IMO.\r\n\r\nEmerica Hsu-Really good flick, weak ollie area, not too good impact support, grip flattened but it didnt matter, still great! sole de-laminated from the shoe. shoe gooed it back and is still skatable. outsole wore fast.\r\n\r\nEmerica herman 2- probably my fav, durable toe, but kind of weak ollie area shoe goo helped. unnecessary stitching but idc. Great flick, semi-good impact support, good boardfeel for a cupsole, and looks plain ol'' sick as hell. also nice grip.', 517, 430, 0, '2009-06-01 18:30:00'),
(3533, 'I have Circa 205 destroyers they have a rubber toe cap with a heel air bag and some kind of ollie underlay thing. I recently bought some shoe goo to put on em before i start skating with them. will they last long?', 517, 1455, 0, '2009-06-17 18:30:00'),
