(3536, 'Globe finales-really good shoe good grip didnt wear out fast nice insole\r\nCirca 211b- good board feel toe wore away really quick and lost grip instantly\r\ncirca 805l- no feel comfy toe blew out immediatly lost almost the whole outsole in a week\r\nAdio eugene refined- bulky stiff wears away\r\netnies cinch- good board feel toe wears out instantly keeps grip for a while', 517, 1457, 0, '2009-07-19 18:30:00'),
(3537, 'es avers-girl edition\r\nverry good shoe it''s hard to do anything in at first but when thet get broken in they are godly....i would give them a 9/10 because at the beginingwhen you get them thay are hard to break in', 517, 1458, 0, '2009-07-25 18:30:00'),
(3538, 'vans TNT II mid: good shoe, broke in pretty easily, the rubber on vans always seems to wear down pretty quickly but a little shoe goo easily fixes that. the grip is solid, lasted me a while, really comfortable. before i got them i was expecting them to be a little tight in the toe area but they were just right. very similar to the half cabs but with better heel padding (they have PU insoles)8/10\r\n\r\nfallen troopers: THE most durable shoe i;ve ever skated. lasted over 3 months of reasonable amount of skating. very comfortable once broken in. the ONLY bad thing was they were a little bulky at times. also not vulcanized which i loved. 9/10', 517, 1459, 0, '2009-07-27 18:30:00'),
(3539, 'Fallen fortes: 8/10\r\nDurable shoe in the beginning, but rips up really easily.\r\nHas great comfort and is a slim fit to your foot.\r\nhas some boardfeel, and it was just the right amount.\r\nIn the beginning it protected you from high drops, but after a while the sole wore down.\r\nDon''t underestimate this shoe, it can be a really good skate shoe, but it will rip up really easily.', 517, 1460, 0, '2009-07-27 18:30:00'),
(3540, 'fallen patriots: these were pretty good shoes. they lasted seriously like a whole year, but i cant really tell because i wasnt skating at all in the winter and in the spring it rained a lot so i couldnt skate much then either. i wore them all school year anyways. they had pretty mediocre grip; not amazing but not bad. it wore down a while back. they seemed extremely bulky at first though until i got used to them/they got broken in. board feel was meh. 7/10', 517, 325, 0, '2009-07-28 18:30:00'),
(3541, 'Globe Magnums- honestly probably the best shoe I have ever had\r\nPeople on this forum told me they were shitty, but they have held up very very long, have fantastic grip, are extremely comfortable, are pretty slim to your feet for boardfeel, they are just all around great shoes\r\nI love them and are bummed out I will have to stop using them soon\r\nand they look sick too\r\n\r\n10/10', 517, 1461, 0, '2009-07-28 18:30:00'),
