(3547, 'some pair of vans my mom got at kohls with the stupid checkers on them and what not..... pretty comfortable shoes with good board feel. not very durable considering i just started skating and it didnt take me very long at all to open it up and my toes were sticking out.\r\n\r\nnike air insurgents- pretty good shoes durable and felt good. i dont remember much about this shoe actually but i think i liked it...\r\n\r\nfallen troopers- awesome durable shoe, extremely comfortable when broken in, feels like slippers, good board feel, and medium grip i guess.\r\n\r\nfallen chiefs- THE GREATEST SHOE EVER. took me about a half hour to break these in, relatively durable, great board feel, awesome grip. you can get these pretty cheap too in some places like 30 bucks.\r\n\r\nreynolds 3''s- just got these yesterday and in the process of breaking them in. havnt skated them yet cause its raining\r\nedit: these shoes are also amazing... i literally didnt have to brake these in to start skating just as good as i did with my last shoes. even learned fakie half cab heels... pretty awesome', 517, 1466, 0, '2009-08-28 18:30:00'),
