(3549, 'Quote:\r\nOriginally Posted by sk8dukedudez\r\nWhat''s a shoe that is very durable, the laces don''t rip easliy, and the nose of the shoe doesn''t get a giant hole in?\r\nthis seems like a riddle...\r\nlook for a pair that has one of those protector things that you can put your lace under, such as the emerica hsus which i hear is very durable.\r\nand the only reason your shoes get giant holes in it is because of the way you skate. Mine used to do the same thing now they evenly wear on the flicking side', 517, 1466, 0, '2009-08-28 18:30:00'),
(3550, 'Quote:\r\nOriginally Posted by Skatingreal\r\nthis seems like a riddle...\r\nlook for a pair that has one of those protector things that you can put your lace under, such as the emerica hsus which i hear is very durable.\r\nand the only reason your shoes get giant holes in it is because of the way you skate. Mine used to do the same thing now they evenly wear on the flicking side\r\n\r\nThe hsus fall apart in like 2 seconds. I don''t know where you all are hearing this false information. The other day I was reading this forum, and someone said, "the reynold 3''s have no boardfeel."', 517, 1468, 0, '2009-08-30 18:30:00'),
