(3556, 'Etnies Clinch\r\n\r\nI have had these shoes for 6 months and they are hella comfy, have an exellent board feel, slide and flick perfectly, are really durable and the grip lasts ages. And the bad part is that little flat spots appear but i have skated these for six months and only 3 little flat spots on the grip appeared. I would reccomend these to all skaters whether your advanced or beginner. Overall an exellent shoe.', 517, 771, 0, '2009-10-04 18:30:00'),
(3557, 'MJ-2 Selects.\r\nIve skated them for 5 days and theyre almost dead. Ive really been focusing on kickflip variations lately but still 5 days is just silly. They skate great though. Lace protection lacks a heap. Im on my 3rd lace now. The grip is great. No holes or anything yet but the toe cap has worn down so much. Shoes usually last me 1 and a half months but these havent lasted even half a month. They''ll be done by the end of the week.', 517, 1472, 0, '2009-10-05 18:30:00'),
(3558, 'Nike Bruins\r\n\r\nSkated them for about 4 weeks now.\r\nThey are holding up, but without shoe goo they would probably have some decent holes in them. The grip is AMAZING, my last lakai''s grip got a hole in them and completely flattened out, while these nikes are still in perfect condition. Literally, hasnt been ground down at all. And if your wondering, I do a fair few tres and scooping tricks. The flick is great as they are a fairly pointy shoe. Impact support is ok, they arent bulky or anything (which I like), but they arent super thin either.', 517, 341, 0, '2009-10-05 18:30:00'),
(3559, 'Nike SB Prod 1 - sick ass shoe, light, durable, grippy, comfy, but my airbag popped or something the sole caved in hella wierd\r\n\r\nNike SB Blazers - What is there to say their blazers comfy, durable, so much grip 3 mid, 4 low\r\n\r\nNike Mark - Another classic, mids are one of my most popular shoe ive had like 5 you stomp the shit out of things, if they could last a little longer they be better\r\n\r\nNike SB Tre A.D - not another shoe like it, durable last forever, healthy for your feet their comfy have a primo block and like suped up for like running, the toe cap makes you flip different gives you control of your feet, if you want a shoe for durability and skatebility these are perfect, like after a while of skating you get tired of them like ive had these shoes forever ive had 2 also\r\n\r\nFallen Ripper - these skate like a beast, they make your tricks look clean, and the flick is on que have had 3 pairs\r\n\r\nFallen Chief - kinda like the rippers but different fit and feel, but they shred\r\n\r\neS accel - only es ive ever had there a puffy shoe but no bulk and last forever. 3 pairs\r\n\r\nEmerica KSL dos - these shoes are comfy great impact support, monster flip, not that durable like prolly a month\r\n\r\nEmerica AR slim - well rounded shoe there made for stomping fo sho\r\n\r\nVans chukka''s - best vans shoe ever hella kickback shoe then skatable i love skating bowls and pools with these love the boardfeel and they last longer than most vans, they can skate anything, 6 pairs\r\n\r\nIve had other shoe but the reviews are pretty much all the same i got my shoes for stomping and my shoes for boardfeel and grip\r\nsome other good shoes ive had\r\nAddias campus vulc\r\nFallen rising sun se\r\nNike SB team edition\r\nCirca 99 vulc\r\nLakai Kost one\r\nEmerica Hsu''s\r\nNike SB harbor\r\nCirca ramondetta\r\nEs Rodrigo tx', 517, 1473, 0, '2009-10-19 18:30:00'),
