(3562, 'vans halfcab pro-great boardfeel super grippy last long as fuck\r\nvans rowley shambles-favorite shoe i''ve had only model of shoe i have liked enough to buy more than once i have 4 pairs\r\nsupra vulk low- decent boardfeel average grip great impact support amazingly comfortable\r\nadio snaps-good shoe good boardfeel great impact support very comfortable lasted me i think 4-5months till the grip just one day went and it was slippery weird but after that i stopped skating em\r\nlakai telfords-good boardfeel good grip lasts awhile great ankle support', 517, 769, 0, '2009-10-20 18:30:00'),
(3563, 'Etnies RVM - Super awesome when you first get them. I felt a little something doing my first set with them, but it didn''t really hurt. They rip really fast, though, and the grip dies just as quickly.\r\n\r\nVans Sk8-Hi - Dunno why I even bought these (at all or as skate shoes). The grip was really good for the first two weeks, but it dies out afterwards, but not totally, it''s just not as obvious. Ankle support is pretty damn good though, ripped in about a month.\r\n\r\nOther honorable mentions\r\n\r\nNike SB Zoom Tre A.D.\r\nCirca Ramondetta''s', 517, 1475, 0, '2009-10-24 18:30:00'),
