(3582, 'CONS Pappalardo Pro\r\nGreat grip, flick, suede, classy.', 517, 214, 0, '2011-04-06 18:30:00'),
(3583, 'Emerica Herman 2''s - the grip never flattens. It amazed me. Takes a good amount of time to rip, but I like shoes with boardfeel and the boardfeel was crappy. Great for stairs though, you''ll never bruise your heel.\r\n\r\nEmerica g codes - best shoe I''ve ever had, grip was the same as Herman 2''s look better and last longer. The boardfeel wasn''t that good but still okay...\r\n\r\nCons cts - wonderful board feel, doesn''t rip for shit, they feel like your stepping on marshmallows or something. I didn''t like the toe cap though because I like a big toe.\r\n\r\nDvs Rico - I love these shoes so much. They have the best board feel ever, nice heel bruise tech. So you don''t bruise your heels easy. They take a good amount of time to rip. Don''t last that long though. If these lasted as long as the g codes then it would be the perfect shoe in my opinion.\r\n\r\nThere''s tons more but I just can''t remember.', 517, 1483, 0, '2011-05-27 18:30:00'),
(3584, 'nike sb janoski:\r\nthese had amazing board feel and lasted a good 4 months, the toe cap ripped pretty easy but i put shoe goo on and they lasted fine\r\n\r\nNike sb bruin:\r\nthis is my favorite shoe. the sole lasted about 4-5 months and the toecap has a little shelltoe thing so they took at least 2 months to rip. these are really nice to skate in and take about 2 hours to break in. good boardfeel aswell\r\n\r\nemerica romero:\r\nthis was a nice shoe to skate in but the sole flattened out in about 2 weeks and the toecap ripped in a week, nice to skate in but only lated a month.\r\n\r\nAdidas skate:\r\nthis is a really low-cut shoe that has pretty much no padding, less than the janoskis. the toecap ripped pretty quick and the sloe has flattened after 6 weeks.\r\n\r\nlakai jericho:\r\nthis was n amazing shoe to skate in but lasted me 2 weeks. the toe cap ripped in the first day and the sole went in 2 weeks. horrible durability.\r\n\r\nglobe ???\r\nthese were my first shoes, they lasted about 6 months but this may be because i was a beginner then. they were quite chunky aswell.\r\n\r\netnies malto:\r\nthese were nice sohes but like the lakais ripped quick. the sole lasted a good monh and a half though.', 517, 1484, 0, '2011-06-09 18:30:00'),
(3585, 'eS Square Two - One of the best shoes I''ve ever had. Everything is good about it. I literally have nothing bad to say about it. When you first get them, they feel like walking on a pillow, then maybe after two weeks, it molds to your foot. You might have to shoe goo the sole after it wares down, but maybe like once.\r\n\r\nNike SB Dunk Mids - These are one of my favorite shoes so far. You''re going to have to break it in, cause'' the grip is not grippy at first, but after that it''s perfect. If you get the old colorways with the straps, it''s pretty annoying, so I''d recommend cutting them off.\r\n\r\nVans Authentics - These are a very good choice for substitution for shoes. If you want to substitute a shoe for maybe a week, this is a pretty good choice. They''re very thin, obviously, so they have a lot of response. Only problem is that it gets a little getting used to on heelflips. Because they''re so thin, it''s kinda hard to flip heelflips. The mid-sole is very grippy, especially in the toe area.\r\n\r\nVans Era Pro - These are not the best in my opinion. They''re good for maybe about two weeks, but then it looses all its grip. I could barely get clean kickflips in these, cause'' the grip wore out so fast. Other than the grip, everything passes a''okay.\r\n\r\nFallen Forte - These were probably one of the worst shoes I''ve ever had. I have pretty wide feet, and they gave me blisters on my toe, it was like a hell skating these. I would''ve retired these, but I wanted to make my money''s worth. The insole feels like there is no insole at all. The heel area was no stable AT ALL. I rolled my ankle in these TWICE. I could barely heelflip in these cause'' it was like skating barefooted. Two things I have to say that''s good about these, it the toe cap and the sole. The toe cap was very good with flip tricks, I think I mastered my bigflips in these and my kickflips were alright. The sole is very flexible and holds up very well, so it stays pretty grippy.\r\n\r\nCons Pappalardo - I don''t really have much to say about these. They''re very good with almost every feature. The breathablity on these were outstanding. My feet were never hot, but I was skating these mainly late winter and early spring.', 517, 1485, 0, '2011-06-30 18:30:00'),
(3586, 'Lakai Brandon Biebel 2 LK-Good grip, good boardfeel, didn''t last long, bad impact support and kinda comfortable.\r\nFallen Revolver VLC- Good grip, Very good boardfeel, lasted me a while, bad impact support and very comfortable.\r\nLakai Telford Low- Good grip but wore out fast, average boardfeel, lasted me a while, average impact support, and very comfortable.', 517, 796, 0, '2011-08-06 18:30:00'),
(3587, 'Vans TNT5: Tony Trujillo''s 5th shoe and a ''pro'' take on the vans claccis ''Old School'' shoe. Wide toe box, even for someone with wide feed like me, I''ve them just about laced so that the eyelet sections are touching each other above the tongue and there is still plenty of room. It''s a wide shoe. Grip is what you''d come to expect from a good pair of Vulcanized Vans. Little to no break-in period needed. Upper eyelet area on my front foot wore down/un-stitched under two weeks due to ollies; sole became thin (lost tread) in the same amount of time on Jessup. Toe caps started to show wear from sliding down a concrete bowl real fast, but what can you do! I highly doubt I will be buying another pair.\r\n\r\nAdidas Businetz Pro: I''m a huge fan of the SAMBA sneaker so these were a no brainer, even though I don''t normally wear cupsoles. Narrow toe box, sort of pointy toe (good for fliks I guess?); I have to wear them pretty loose to not feel cramped/loss of circulation Great board feel and good grip. Ventilated tongue is pretty sweet (especially in conjunction with the Adidas mesh top socks from your local costco), I''m in TX and it''s HOT, the shoes breath well. Cupsole support is real nice even though it took getting used to, with as loose as I have to wear them due to the narrow toe box, I find myself sliding around in the cup, which isn''t ideal. Same ollie wear as listed above, upper eyelets were demolished in a week (same for my second pair); shoe to the rescue. Excellent show with killer looks.', 517, 445, 0, '2011-10-13 18:30:00'),
(3588, 'Vans half cabs - Had lots of pairs of these since I started skating in 1992! Love the vans waffle sole. Appreciate the ankle support. And really durable.\r\n\r\nMy favourite skate shoes of all time are Airwalk Jason Lees. Insane comfort and really simple. Not available anymore.', 517, 1486, 0, '2011-10-21 18:30:00'),
