(3596, 'Emerica G-Codes - These shoes have lasted me about 6 months. They''re pretty worn out, but they are still definitely skateable. The flick area doesn''t tear easily, which is good because my VOX I had before tore after about 2 weeks. The STI foam stays perfect the entire time. Best shoes I''ve had.\r\n\r\nDVS Convict- These shoes aren''t for everyone. They''re vulcanized, but have heel bruise control in the sole. They wear down pretty quick, but I like my shoes to be worn out and torn a bit. After they''re worn down, it hurts to not land on your board, so it helps with commitment.\r\n\r\nDoes anyone know the difference between DC Cole Pro Shoes and DC Cole S Shoes??', 517, 1491, 0, '2012-05-27 18:30:00'),
