(3605, 'Adidas Vulcs: Last VERY long, it took me 14 months to get a hole in the sole, and by that time the entire shoe no longer had any tread on it. The stripes come off fairly easily, but the suede underneath resists holes very well. It''s also the most comfortable shoe I''ve owned.\r\n\r\nVans TNT-5: Oppositely, lasted a miniscule amount of time. In two months there were multiple holes in both soles, the stripe on my left shoe was gone, the area where it was stitched frayed apart to reveal another hole in the side of the upper, and a suede bit that went over the laces on the cuff (?) of the shoe was entirely gone. However, they did work nicely, but are not at all worth it for the price.\r\n\r\nNike Ruckus Mid: Last even shorter than the Vans. I got a refund from my local store because in 22 days they developed a hole in the sole. Every other part of the shoe was sound, except the sole wore away retardedly fast. I didn''t have much time to wear these, so I can''t make a proper review.\r\n\r\nNike Mavrk Low: Last very long as well, about 7 months. They held up very well, and didn''t develop any substantial holes until the last month or so of skating them, and in the usual spots; the ball and outside of my front foot. Overall very nice.\r\n\r\nI just got me some Adidas Busenitz today, haven''t gotten to skate them yet, but I''m pretty stoked.', 517, 474, 0, '2012-09-14 18:30:00'),
