(3611, 'Nike Renzos- From the S to the U to the CK. The grip was absolutely horrible.\r\n\r\nOsiris NYC ''83- Comfortable, Supportive, decent grip. Lasted my first month of skating and the sole is almost worn through\r\n\r\nSupra Skytop 3- Comfortable (the gel pad under the heel is *insane*. You can literally stand in one spot and bounce.), Supportive but you can still move your ankle pretty well, Grip is absolutely insane. Greatest grip *ever.', 517, 1498, 0, '2012-11-10 18:30:00'),
(3612, 'I have Emerica canvases (can''t remember the ''model'', but they''re gray (front)/black (mid-rear) with white bottoms. They started fraying after 5 hours or skating - the lace tore in half and it''s just looking really prematurely shredded (it = flip-foot).\r\n\r\nI just ordered some Emerica G-Codes in Burgandy/Gum so hopefully those, being an obviously more skate-oriented style, will be better overall.', 517, 583, 0, '2013-05-11 18:30:00'),
