(4818, 'Quote:\r\nOriginally Posted by Victor\nAlright, I''ll buy them and put them in a glass case and never even wear them, because thats rational isn''t it? They are actually decently priced on ebay.\r\n\r\nYeah, I love the look of the send helps but I also want a shoe that will last long so I''m quite torn.\r\nBecause thats what I said? I wear my legit prod futuras to school if it matches my outfit, but I don''t skate them because thats just stupid. Why spend a decent ammount of money on hard to get shoes just to put holes in them and make them dirty. If you want a dunk high that lasts long get khakis for cheap.\r\n\r\n*edit* I looked on ebay, Basically 90% of the send helps are fake. I saw about 5 different sellers with the same blurry insole picture.', 518, 1507, 0, '2006-09-15 18:30:00'),
(4819, 'Quote:\r\nOriginally Posted by Victor\nwhy do your guy''s shoes have to be legit? aret you just gonna end up skating them anyways?\r\nFake shoes support an asshole who makes hundreds of dollars from some shit he made in his basement, and he can continue making fake shoes, and they will fall apart in a week. And if you buy collectors 300$+ shoes, again, its just stupid to skate them.', 518, 1507, 0, '2006-09-15 18:30:00'),
