(4821, 'Quote:\r\nOriginally Posted by Victor\nHow can you tell they are fake? If its the same picture and the same seller mabey he does not want to take pictures of each shoe that looks exactally the same.\r\nI meant 5 different people selling send helps had the same blurry insole picture as the other sellers. And as a rule of thumb, you never buy from a seller with only 2 low quality pictures anyway, legit sellers know legit buyers want pictures of the tags, tongues, sole, etc.\r\n\r\nIf send helps arent atleast above 100 they are fake. And looks can be decieving.\r\nhttp://cgi.ebay.com/Nike-Dunk-High-P...QQcmdZViewItem\r\nThose have high quality pictures, and look real. But the guy is selling other fake shoes, the price is too low, and the shoes have small but noticable defects. And a legit check on nikeskateboarding.org said they are fake. Im not trying to be a ass, just warning you ebay isent the best place to buy SBs. People go to extremely great lengths to make fake shoes seem legit.\r\n\r\nlook at how the sole is attached to the shoe, the swoosh is minorly stitched wrong, but it should be near or actually perfect. the lines on the back should be again, almost perfectly parralel. everythings sloppy and not straight on a fake.\r\n\r\n\r\non a real its nice and straight and clean.', 518, 1507, 0, '2006-09-15 18:30:00'),
