(10952, 'Quote:\r\nOriginally Posted by Regina!!!\r\nSo, you just got a new pair of trucks and you think there to loose or tight? Well I have made a guide just for you.\r\n\r\nTo tight your trucks this is what you need,\r\nTrucks (of course)\r\nskate tool, 15mm wrench or 15mm socket wrench.\r\n1. get your 15mm wrench or skatetool.\r\n2. get your trucks\r\n3. if the trucks are not on your deck please do so now.\r\n4. put the wrench or skatetool on the king pin.\r\n5. if there to tight turn it left. if there to loose turn it to the right.\r\n6. stand on your bored and try them out.\r\n7. if there not how you want them just adjust them.\r\n\r\nHere is a pic that might help.\r\n\r\n\r\nHope this helps you.\r\nQuote:\r\nOriginally Posted by CJ Lee\r\n........ How do you loosen them 0_o\r\nI wonder....?', 537, 266, 0, '2014-01-30 18:30:00'),
