(10973, 'if you measured 19.5cm axle length there likely to be 7.75 inch axles which are best for boards around 7.5 - 8 inches wide. the height of the trucks is measured from the bottom of the baseplate to the center of the axle, low trucks will be around 47mm high, mids will be around 49-52, and high trucks are generally 55mm and taller.\r\n\r\nas for the the photo they are speed washers, they go either side of your wheel you actually want 8 of them not 4. most skate shops should sell them. if there is no local shops around try online shops in the spare parts section.', 540, 1092, 0, '2014-04-28 18:30:00'),
