(11001, 'Quote:\r\nOriginally Posted by Lailah\nHow could Song, Mullen and the rest be wrong? ;)\r\nSkateboarding logic doesn''t apply to those two. As for the rest, I''d be genuinely surprised if the majority of them actually rode Tensors, because hell knows most pros don''t actually ride their sponsored trucks.', 542, 378, 0, '2014-01-14 18:30:00'),
(11002, 'My last set of trucks before my current ones (which were part of the crappy complete i''m currently riding) were Tensor trucks, and i never had any problems with them at all.\r\n\r\nThey lasted me years without any issues. I can''t say i liked them that much, but they did the job.\r\nAdmittedly they were pretty beaten up... But what trucks wouldn''t be?\r\n\r\n\r\nFor how cheap Tensors are you can''t do wrong. There are MUCH better trucks out there, but for the cost they''ll do you fine.\r\nAnd as Martha has said, with names like Daewon Song and Joey Brezinski on the roster they can''t be that bad!', 542, 222, 0, '2014-01-14 18:30:00'),
(11003, 'Had a pair,broke them in no time.Like 3 months worth of skating.Never going to buy tensor again.', 542, 435, 0, '2014-01-14 18:30:00'),
(11004, 'Tensors grind down fast, and their bushings become pancakes after a few sessions but they turn nice and grind smoother than any trick I''ve had. But make sure to get the response model. Not the slider, that shit is horrid.', 542, 819, 0, '2014-01-15 18:30:00'),
