(11010, 'But i have silver trucks on now, they''re amazing no matter what people say. Only done 50-50 and 5-0''s on them though so I wont know what it''s like with other grinds.', 542, 265, 0, '2014-01-20 18:30:00'),
(11011, 'Quote:\r\nOriginally Posted by Lailah\nDidn''t they go tits up in 2010?\r\nNo idea when exactly when they went out of business. All I remember is making fun of how ridiculously gimmicky they were. Curved baseplates? I think they made some stupid hubcap kind of thing to cover your bearings. Their idea to make the kingpin a lot lower than the hanger was a cool idea in theory, only they went all dumb and used a flat allen bolt that you couldn''t tighten. I think they event went so far as to start making composite baseplates too. Just ridiculous. Now that I''m thinking about it...Fury Trucks were pretty stupid too.', 542, 1091, 0, '2014-01-20 18:30:00'),
(11012, 'I always thought Grind Kings seemed dumb too.\r\n\r\nAnyway, I had a pair of Tensors, and I had no issues with them. I skated Ventures exclusively all through the 90s and early 2000s. In 2011, I bought a set of Indys, which is what I ride now. I bought the Tensors when I needed some 8.25s, and apparently Indy does not make any in that size. I got ''em, skated ''em, had no problems.\r\n\r\nHowever, if Indy makes the size I want at the moment, I will always go that way these days.', 542, 1987, 0, '2014-01-20 18:30:00'),
(11013, 'Quote:\r\nOriginally Posted by Midwest_Mike\r\nNo idea when exactly when they went out of business. All I remember is making fun of how ridiculously gimmicky they were. Curved baseplates? I think they made some stupid hubcap kind of thing to cover your bearings. Their idea to make the kingpin a lot lower than the hanger was a cool idea in theory, only they went all dumb and used a flat allen bolt that you couldn''t tighten. I think they event went so far as to start making composite baseplates too. Just ridiculous. Now that I''m thinking about it...Fury Trucks were pretty stupid too.\r\nOh i agree with you 100% that they were gimmicky, that''s a fact.\r\nI guess skating has just moved on a lot in the last decade.', 542, 222, 0, '2014-01-20 18:30:00'),
(11014, 'Quote:\r\nOriginally Posted by Ukins\r\nAnyone like these? I''ve been using thunders but i tried my friends skateboard with tensors and i really liked them. But i''ve only tried them once so i was wondering how good they are long term? And what kind should i get?\r\nhorrible trucks.', 542, 1099, 0, '2014-01-20 18:30:00'),
