INSERT INTO `responses` (`id`, `content`, `postid`, `userid`, `havemedia`, `response_timestamp`) VALUES
(11035, 'Kinda rising this post from the graveyard, but there is a reason i''ll explain at the finish of this post\r\n\r\nSo, a lot of time has passed, and I made a few all alluminium trucks that was reaaaly light, like paper weight..\r\n\r\nFirst thing first..\r\n\r\n1) The kingpin isn''t higher than the hanger, the pictures just make it look like it is.\r\n\r\n2) I made the first truck by mind-generated geometry, with a normal steel bar, and it handles and rides well but it looks sh*t.. the one in the picture was made looking at an Indipendent truck( can''t remeber the exact name) and this was the best I have done at that time.\r\n\r\n3) YES, i have made homemade bushings, from a hard type of rubber.like material( its not rubber, but kind of) its equivalent to other bushings is 90-92A, so its medium hard.. and it handles like magic, it even acts as a bumper as its rubber kind of material, and I don''t even feel the small holes on the road\r\n\r\n4)The baseplates: On the first(shitty) truck, my friend has casted for me the baseplates. And they were good at first, but one started to crack. On the truck on the pictures up here, I Mathewhined them on my mill, and they still hold and ride well..\r\n\r\n5) Its all connected as a normal skateboard truck, basically it is like any other truck, just lighter and more durable.( as it isn''t casted, but MIG welded)\r\n\r\n\r\nTHe reason i am waking this post from the deads is:\r\n\r\n1st: I have seen a lot of skate dudes asking about custom made trucks, and I already sold the aluminium ones to a dude in my city, and they still ride and glide well.\r\n\r\n2nd: I had connection problems at the time I posted this, and when i fixed them, i forgot that i posted this thread. But now you will see more and more homemade and DIY projects for skateboards from me, and I even got a GoPro Hero 3+, so pictures will be pretty badass.\r\n\r\nAsk me anything, now im available, and thanks for the support guys!\r\n\r\n\r\nP.S: To the haters: since i posted this thread, in 2012, i still ride with that trucks, so well.. 10 stairs wouldn''t be so hard,huh?', 543, 1988, 0, '2014-04-28 18:30:00'),
(11036, 'can you post some of your new designs? this is actually really interesting', 543, 276, 0, '2014-04-28 18:30:00'),
(11037, 'Im sorry, but I sold the new ones i made, and didn''t take photos of them.. Perhaps i could try to find the 3D model I made of them.. Thanks!', 543, 1988, 0, '2014-04-28 18:30:00'),
