(11059, 'Comments in Blue!\r\n\r\nQuote:\r\nOriginally Posted by Lailah\nI''m looking at trying a pair of aces (probably the 8'' hanger ones, I think they are the 33''s). I''m downsizing from indy 149''s and getting a slightly smaller deck (probably an 8.18).\r\n\r\nACE 44s are 8.25" wide, just a tad wider than your 8.18" might want to consider them...0.035 of axle sticking out is nothing\r\n\r\n1) How do Aces ride compared to Indy''s?\r\nACEs are based off Indy Stage III geometry, they''re in the same family so to speak; ACE turn quicker than Indy, are much lighter and come with stock bushing you can actually skate\r\n\r\n2) Will they suffice as a street truck? I do skate mostly tranny but am getting into street as well, so I need something that can cope with all situations.\r\n\r\nYes. However, ACE are very turny trucks, and excel at tranny, you might need to tighten them more than you think you should to get them where you want them for street (I always have to loosen them up if I take a street board with aces to a bowl)\r\n\r\n3) Do the bones hard bushing fit right into aces? And is it worth switching out the bushings for bones hardcore hards? (I normally ride the Indy''s loose but with the hard bushings if ya know what I mean).\r\n\r\nBones Bushings fit ACEs just fine, regardless of hardness. I ride loose and I found that riding Bones Hards in my ACE LOs was ideal, especially when the hards broke in, I still prefer Bones Mediums in Standard ACEs, the hards take too long to break in.\r\n\r\nCheers!', 547, 445, 0, '2014-03-10 18:30:00'),
(11060, 'Could not have asked for a better answer, much appreciated!', 547, 1996, 0, '2014-03-10 18:30:00'),
(11061, 'How do Aces grind vs Indy on coping? I used G&S steel trucks for years and it turns out that they grind very slow compared to my new setup with Mini Logos. Loving the mini logos on my 8" and 8.25" boards. I have skated a buddy''s deck with Indys and am planning on getting a new setup with similar trucks for bigger transition. Looking at Indy 159s and Ace 55s. Other option would be a Theeve CSX 6.5, or just say screw it and get Mini Logo 8.75s with risers.', 547, 1094, 0, '2014-03-11 18:30:00'),
