(11076, 'Quote:\r\nOriginally Posted by Shannon\nTensors are the best at not turning.\r\nQuote:\r\nOriginally Posted by Martha\r\nI know some guys who like Tensors, but they don''t turn, I had a buddy who broke several pairs, and I rode a pair, and they just don''t feel good to me.\r\nQuote:\r\nOriginally Posted by Air\r\nOh shit.\r\nNow my thoughts on Tensors just changed so much.\r\nHaha I will stay with Thunders as long as possible, they just feel best for me. Even better than Indy''s.\r\nHA! tell that shit to DAEWON or RODNEY motha fuckas......but ooooookay.\r\nyall should look them up, really.\r\n\r\n\r\nEither way the 2 pairs I had 4 years ago had no problems turning (its on me.....wtf) and lasted. But of course theres preference so if its hard to turn then of course youd want something I guess that does it for you even though in the end its on you.\r\n\r\nThat was 4yrs ago. But turning with trucks, neeeever had the problem I guess idgaf since its for me to do. I don''t know I guess if I felt the problem (because a loooot of ppl do, that''s cool) then im sure itd annoy me for those sharp ass corners? I don''t get it, then again I don''t have to. Its for the rider to decide. But I don''t struggle to turn? every truck gets it done ive had. ( I do ride loose, but the tensors were tight)\r\n\r\nIm lost, unless its just a little thing bugged out about, or if its a biggg deal. either I never experienced it, or its so irrelevant that I never noticed.', 548, 279, 0, '2014-03-04 18:30:00'),
(11077, 'Mullen doesn''t turn...and daewon doesn''t even use top bushings, he''s exempt from the conversation.\r\n\r\nI rode a pair of tensors a few years ago, yes the can turn but compared to other trucks, say indy, ace or theeve, they don''t turn nearly as good.\r\n\r\nIf you ride tight trucks, I am sure they would be great for you, but then, any truck would.\r\n\r\nQuote:\r\nOriginally Posted by MartyRules\r\nTheeves over everything\r\nQuote:\r\nOriginally Posted by BMCsteve\r\nThis. I''m totally sold on Theeve after a week\r\nGlad to see they are working out for you dude, hell of a truck huh?', 548, 445, 0, '2014-03-04 18:30:00'),
(11078, 'Quote:\r\nOriginally Posted by Martha\r\nMullen doesn''t turn...and daewon doesn''t even use top bushings, he''s exempt from the conversation.\r\n\r\nI rode a pair of tensors a few years ago, yes the can turn but compared to other trucks, say indy, ace or theeve, they don''t turn nearly as good.\r\n\r\nIf you ride tight trucks, I am sure they would be great for you, but then, any truck would.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nGlad to see they are working out for you dude, hell of a truck huh?\r\nagain, I get wheel bite standing on my board LITERALLY(sorry if I didn''t tell you that, maybe it was someone else)\r\nand Rodney does turn.....a lot actually. and so does daweon, sure ONE is lose beyond belief but THE OTHER ISNT and he uses BOTH SIDES constantly....so yeah they do.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nAs far as the turn thing goes whats the MAJOR difference or is it a little bitching type thing (not like that but as in its really not affecting you) I just don''t see how they are majorly different in turning response/ why it matters......\r\n\r\nIve never had the problem so im asking is it NOTICABLE majorly, or is it more of a little thing(that may be big to ppl personally?) I don''t get the whole thing.....? uness its because its not that big a deal (but that depends on the person) aint trying to sell you on Tensors or nothing or argue(because its WHAT YOU WANT), just curious because this is not the first ive heard of trucks not turning good but don''t get it.\r\n\r\n*speed racer, are yall?', 548, 279, 0, '2014-03-04 18:30:00'),
