(11158, 'I totally agree, the old street corner distrubution bushings were complete shit until broken in. Bushings in these new ventures from deluxe are pretty awsome, I prefer them to bones bushings without a doubt, they feel more stable and you can still ride them loose enough to get a turn on. I rode my mates magenta and it felt awsome, sadly there like 110 bucks in aus so I wont be getting one any time soon.\r\n\r\nI hate how people are to arrogant to give venture a try, I think they are sex after these thunder lows Ima go back to ventures no doubt', 551, 436, 0, '2014-02-23 18:30:00'),
(11159, 'I don''t get how some people hate Venture even though they ride Thunders. I''ve never tried Venture, but since they''re DLX (All I ride are Thunders), why not give them a try? That''s like saying you love Real boards but hate Anti-Hero...', 551, 1107, 0, '2014-02-23 18:30:00'),
(11160, 'Quote:\r\nOriginally Posted by Shannon\nI don''t get how some people hate Venture even though they ride Thunders. I''ve never tried Venture, but since they''re DLX (All I ride are Thunders), why not give them a try? That''s like saying you love Real boards but hate Anti-Hero...\r\n\r\n.......Which is plausible, seeing as they have different shapes.\r\n\r\nI won''t ride Flip, Santa Cruz, or Krux, which are all under NHS. I do ride Creature and Independent. Just because you like a distribution will not mean you''re going to like every company under them.', 551, 259, 0, '2014-02-24 18:30:00'),
