(11204, 'Trying to find a wheel that is all terrain, smooth for cruising and is still "good to skate" is a pretty tall order. When it comes to the OJ Hot Juice and Spitfire 80HD''s it''s impossible to say which is "better." They''re both really different from each other. The Hot Juice wheels really wide, soft, smooth and fast. The Spitfire 80HD''s are just a softer version the Spitfire Classic wheel. Labeling them a "cruiser" wheel is a bit misleading. It''s really meant to smooth out extremely rough spots. They pretty much skate like your average hard wheel. If you want a good wheel that falls in in between check out the Krooked Zip Zinger wheels, I have a 65mm set and they''re really fast and have held up well to the abuse I''ve put them through.', 559, 1091, 0, '2014-04-28 18:30:00'),
(11205, 'na bra, its pretty normal, I had that on my last few sets of spit classics', 560, 436, 0, '2014-04-28 18:30:00'),
