(11220, 'I skate 58mm classics on my everyday setup. I''m used to and prefer to skate larger wheels...I don''t skate anything under 56mm. I''ve got a set of older spitfire classic 80d''s and they''re the exact same shape as a standard classic wheel. From the pictures of the Spitfire/Supreme collaboration I''ve seen, they''re just a set of spitfire 80HD''s with the Supreme name on them. I don''t know why anyone would want to be associated with that brand, but to each their own. Again...there doesn''t seem to be a difference between the Spitfire/Supreme wheels and the regular Spitfire 80HD wheels.', 564, 1091, 0, '2014-04-28 18:30:00'),
