(11227, 'They''re called "classics" for a reason. I must have had around 3 pairs of the 52mm classics and I loved them. Contrary to popular belief, they DID NOT flatspot on the first week I got them. However, F4s are probably the best wheels on the market, so if I were you, I''d get another pair of those.', 566, 1107, 0, '2014-03-22 18:30:00'),
(11228, 'imagine what good ol'' basic wheels would feel like and that''s what you get. it has none of "technology" of the newer harder wheels but still amazing only if they didn''t shrink down so quickly. f4''s are beast though. they improved on all the issues I had with the classics and turned em into super wheels.', 566, 447, 0, '2014-03-23 18:30:00'),
(11229, 'Quote:\r\nOriginally Posted by TheAwkwardCanadian\r\nThey''re called "classics" for a reason. I must have had around 3 pairs of the 52mm classics and I loved them. Contrary to popular belief, they DID NOT flatspot on the first week I got them. However, F4s are probably the best wheels on the market, so if I were you, I''d get another pair of those.\r\nThis. I''m on my 4th set myself. It''s probably one of the best wheels on the market. They got it right and haven''t changed it. I''ve never had flatspots on any of them, I''ve never had a flatspot on any wheel.', 566, 1091, 0, '2014-03-23 18:30:00'),
(11230, 'They were all I''d ever skate until the F4''s came out, now I have a new fave wheel.', 566, 1996, 0, '2014-03-24 18:30:00'),
