(11495, 'Quote:\r\nOriginally Posted by Krish\nUsually the harder core rolls faster due to less friction. The softer outer absorbs more vibrations for a smoother ride. I have a set that I love.\r\nThis.\r\n\r\nCouple a hard inner core and hard outer and you''ve got a wicked fast wheel that is hard as well. I think that the ricta chrome cores are as hard as anyone should skate.\r\n\r\nAlso, the core provides a correct/proper bearing seat which enables a faster roll (provided it isn''t crooked and causing the wheel to wobble).\r\n\r\nNot all cores are created equal; I had two sets of satoris that were off (recycled cores).\r\n\r\nCored wheels that rock:\r\n\r\nLandEmilee (I wish I could find a set that are 55mm+ that aren''t sidecuts).\r\nType-S\r\nPi\r\nAutobahn (COME ON AB dudes, make 55mm+ again)\r\nRainskates', 586, 445, 0, '2013-12-14 18:30:00'),
