(11534, 'I hated the 100s I rode, got them for $10 w/free shipping so I figured what the hell why not.\r\n\r\nAt parks they felt slow, didn''t chirp when I slid them, on rough street they seemed ok, if a bit soft (but they were 100s).\r\n\r\nAs mentioned above, spend a few bucks more and get F4s or STFs or something from smaller companies like autobahn/gold/sml/momentum/landshark/portland/etc.', 590, 445, 0, '2013-12-27 18:30:00'),
(11535, 'ok i have riden stfs and 100s. the 100s dont ware but other than that they suck buy stfs', 590, 437, 0, '2014-01-05 18:30:00'),
(11536, 'Big\r\n\r\nBones SPF 58 mill. They don''t wear down that much.', 591, 259, 0, '2013-12-26 18:30:00'),
(11537, 'smaller like 50-52\r\nright now I''m riding some bones 52 STF\r\nthey haven''t really worn down much yet tho, but they''re starting to', 591, 1116, 0, '2013-12-26 18:30:00'),
(11538, 'I like 52-. I''m currently riding 51mms.', 591, 267, 0, '2013-12-26 18:30:00'),
(11539, 'my last pair of wheels were some 52 elements and I rode them really long, they ended up about 50mm. I just got a pair of 50mm Ricta Chrome-Cores a few hours ago so I can''t say how long they''ll last', 591, 1093, 0, '2013-12-26 18:30:00'),
(11540, 'i like wheels in the middle i ride 54''s i dont want too small or too big, mainly i dont want to get too big cuz the you will be higher off the ground and i like riding lower and too small you dont cover as much ground in each push', 591, 1879, 0, '2013-12-26 18:30:00'),
(11541, 'Quote:\r\nOriginally Posted by RJ_SK8\r\nmy last pair of wheels were some 52 elements and I rode them really long, they ended up about 50mm. I just got a pair of 50mm Ricta Chrome-Cores a few hours ago so I can''t say how long they''ll last\r\nI had a pair of Elements once, they were the Featherlights. They got to about 50-51mm and one of the bearing holders on the wheels busted.', 591, 267, 0, '2013-12-26 18:30:00'),
(11542, 'hahaha I just got some Bones 100s and I think theyre good theyre 53 mm and I cant wait until they wear down,but itll be a while', 591, 475, 0, '2013-12-26 18:30:00'),
(11543, 'I''ll ride Bones STF V2 and V3 or Spitfire Formula Fours.\r\nAnything between 51-53 mm', 591, 1126, 0, '2013-12-26 18:30:00'),
(11544, 'I like my wheels big. I''m currently skating 58mm Spitfire classics...and 56mm Mini Logo wheels on my back up board. I only skate street, but the roads/spots here are super rough. A little 52mm wheel wouldn''t work for shit here. I also don''t drive to spots, it would be miserable to push a tiny wheel across town.', 591, 1091, 0, '2013-12-30 18:30:00'),
(11545, 'I''m riding Bones STF 50s. They were the last pair of wheels in the shop so I had to grab em. But I''ll ride bigger STFs if I could get any. Shit''s really good.', 591, 1489, 0, '2013-12-30 18:30:00'),
(11546, 'Wider contact patch.', 592, 259, 0, '2013-12-22 18:30:00'),
(11547, 'Quote:\r\nOriginally Posted by Martha\r\nWider contact patch.\r\n...thereby giving you more grip at speed!', 592, 445, 0, '2013-12-22 18:30:00'),
(11548, 'is it good for getting over pool coping', 592, 1099, 0, '2013-12-23 18:30:00'),
(11549, 'I thought SPF and stuff didn''t work too well at pools and vert and stuff, because they were a little too hard.', 592, 267, 0, '2013-12-23 18:30:00'),
(11550, 'They are wicked fast in bowls.', 592, 445, 0, '2013-12-23 18:30:00'),
(11551, 'Quote:\r\nOriginally Posted by Martha\r\nThey wicked fast in bowls.\r\nDo they slide too much because they''re so hard though?', 592, 267, 0, '2013-12-23 18:30:00'),
(11552, 'Quote:\r\nOriginally Posted by Jadyn\nDo they slide too much because they''re so hard though?\r\n\r\nOnly on Masonite or something similar. Concrete they''re grippy as all get out.', 592, 259, 0, '2013-12-23 18:30:00'),
(11553, 'bones stf is the perfect street wheel', 593, 2027, 0, '2013-11-19 18:30:00'),
(11554, 'Spitfire formula four. Best wheels ever, I used to only ride bones stf until I tried out the formula 4''s they are simply amazing and slide better.', 593, 283, 0, '2013-11-19 18:30:00'),
(11555, 'for street I would get a harder wheel like bones and ricta for speed (to clear those gaps/star sets) 50mm-52mm, for an all round sort of setup I would reccomend somthing like spitfire classics or spitfire swirls neither of which are too hard or soft (which would work ok in street terrain and also park) 52mm-54mm, for park only I would reccomend some Oj wheels or some bones spf (they grip/slide perfect for park bowl,tranny use) 54mm-56mm. Hope this helped man :)', 593, 436, 0, '2013-11-19 18:30:00'),
(11556, 'Majorly skateboard wheels are differentiated from the smoothness, size and shape. With the help of durometer scale we can check the hollowness of the wheel. Lower the number, wheels re softer and higher the number, wheels are harder.', 593, 485, 0, '2013-12-16 18:30:00'),
(11557, 'Bones STF for smaller wheels, SPF for bigger.\r\n\r\nI skate street with 58 mm wheels, and I''ve skated STFs in the past. They''re very similar, size is the biggest difference in my opinion.', 593, 259, 0, '2013-12-17 18:30:00'),
(11558, 'Well theres different models of those brands so it depends on which model. I''m sure every one of those brands has a set of wheels that will work for ya. I''ve basically only ridden bones/spitfires in the time I''ve skated.', 594, 383, 0, '2013-12-08 18:30:00'),
(11559, 'Spitfire Classics formula four 99a 56mm', 594, 1495, 0, '2013-12-08 18:30:00'),
(11560, 'Quote:\r\nOriginally Posted by Jadyn\nSpitfire Classics formula four 99a 56mm\r\nI had some they where awesome but too big for my taste', 594, 2028, 0, '2013-12-09 18:30:00'),
(11561, 'The F4s do come in smaller sizes...56, 55, 54, 53, 52 - Full, classic & tablet shapes.', 594, 445, 0, '2013-12-09 18:30:00'),
(11562, 'Quote:\r\nOriginally Posted by Martha\r\nThe F4s do come in smaller sizes...56, 55, 54, 53, 52 - Full, classic & tablet shapes.\r\ni meant just the classics not the formula four''s i got those for free', 594, 2028, 0, '2013-12-09 18:30:00'),
(11563, 'Or go for 55mm full shape formula 4s', 594, 1495, 0, '2013-12-09 18:30:00'),
(11564, 'Quote:\r\nOriginally Posted by Jadyn\nOr go for 55mm full shape formula 4s\r\nI''ve been trying to find a set of these, no luck. Has anyone skated the F4s on tranny, not little park stuff but deep bowls?', 594, 445, 0, '2013-12-10 18:30:00'),
(11565, 'http://bones.com/why/skatepark-formula/\r\nNot that grippy, but is intended for slick parks and stuff.', 594, 267, 0, '2013-12-10 18:30:00'),
(11566, 'DO NOT GET SPFS. you will eat shit skating bowls. they are TOO god damn slippery! they are the hardest wheels out there, a 104 a. sidester is just repeating what the website says, how theyre for slick parks. iv used them at slick parks and its like skating on ice. Get spitfire classics, they grip good and slide good.', 594, 1099, 0, '2013-12-16 18:30:00'),
(11567, 'classics were my favorite wheel- until formula fours came around...', 594, 469, 0, '2013-12-16 18:30:00'),
